const COURSE = {"title": "LuaU Mastery", "subtitle": "The complete Roblox Luau programming course. From absolute beginner to expert — master every concept, library, service, and pattern.", "stats": [{"num": "40", "label": "lessons"}, {"num": "200+", "label": "examples"}, {"num": "40", "label": "quizzes"}, {"num": "100%", "label": "free & open"}], "groups": [{"label": "Start Here", "lessons": [0]}, {"label": "Fundamentals", "lessons": [1, 2, 3, 4]}, {"label": "Data Structures", "lessons": [5, 6, 7, 8]}, {"label": "Advanced Luau", "lessons": [9, 10, 11, 12]}, {"label": "Standard Libraries", "lessons": [13, 14, 15]}, {"label": "Roblox Core", "lessons": [16, 17, 18, 19]}, {"label": "Roblox Advanced", "lessons": [20, 21, 22, 23]}, {"label": "Roblox Services", "lessons": [24, 25, 26, 27]}, {"label": "Service Deep Dives", "lessons": [28, 29, 30, 31]}, {"label": "Expert Services", "lessons": [32, 33, 34, 35]}, {"label": "Debugging & Testing", "lessons": [36, 37, 38]}, {"label": "Capstone", "lessons": [39]}], "lessons": [{"id": 0, "title": "Overview", "icon": "🏠", "color": "#00d4ff", "desc": "Welcome to LuaU Mastery", "isHero": true, "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "👋 Welcome — No Experience Needed!", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "If you've <strong>never written a single line of code before</strong>, you're in the right place. This course starts from absolute zero and walks you through everything step-by-step."}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong style='color:var(--accent)'>What is programming?</strong> Programming is simply giving a computer a set of instructions — like a recipe. You write out the steps, and the computer follows them exactly. That's it! The \"language\" we use to write those instructions for Roblox is called <strong>Luau</strong>."}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong style='color:var(--accent)'>What is Luau?</strong> Luau (pronounced \"Loo-ow\") is Roblox's programming language. Every game you've ever played on Roblox — the menus, the characters, the weapons, the coins — is powered by Luau scripts running behind the scenes. When you learn Luau, you learn to build <em>anything</em> on Roblox."}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "You Don't Need to Memorize Everything", "text": "Nobody memorizes an entire programming language. You learn the patterns, practice them, and look things up when you need to. This course is your reference — come back to any lesson whenever you want."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🖥️ Where Do You Write Code?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "You write Luau code inside <strong>Roblox Studio</strong> — the free app where you build Roblox games. Here's how to get started:"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Step 1:</strong> Download & open <strong>Roblox Studio</strong> (free at create.roblox.com).<br><strong>Step 2:</strong> Create a new <strong>Baseplate</strong> project.<br><strong>Step 3:</strong> In the <strong>Explorer</strong> panel (right side), expand <code>ServerScriptService</code>.<br><strong>Step 4:</strong> Right-click it → Insert Object → <strong>Script</strong>.<br><strong>Step 5:</strong> Double-click the new Script to open it. You'll see <code>print(\"Hello world!\")</code>.<br><strong>Step 6:</strong> Press the <strong>▶ Play</strong> button at the top. Look at the <strong>Output</strong> window at the bottom — it should say \"Hello world!\"."}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "The Output Window", "text": "If you don't see the Output window, go to <strong>View → Output</strong> in the top menu. This is where your <code>print()</code> messages and error messages appear. You'll use it constantly!"}, {"type": "text", "value": "🎉 <strong>Congratulations!</strong> If you did that, you just ran your first program. The <code>print()</code> command tells the computer: \"display this text in the Output window.\" Everything in this course builds on this foundation."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🗺 What is Luau?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong style='color:var(--accent)'>Luau</strong> is a fast, modern programming language built on top of an older language called <strong>Lua 5.1</strong>. Think of it like this: Lua is the foundation, and Luau adds modern features on top (like type checking, better loops, and string interpolation)."}, {"type": "text", "value": "Every script in Roblox runs on Luau. This course covers <strong>everything</strong> — from basic syntax to advanced patterns, all standard libraries, and every important Roblox service and API."}, {"type": "chips", "items": [{"text": "Typed Lua", "color": "blue"}, {"text": "Lua 5.1 compatible", "color": "green"}, {"text": "Open Source", "color": "purple"}, {"text": "Custom VM", "color": "yellow"}, {"text": "Native Codegen", "color": "red"}]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚡ Key Luau Differences from Lua 5.1", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "If you've never used Lua before, don't worry about this section — just know that Luau has some nice extras. If you <em>have</em> used standard Lua, here's what's new:"}, {"type": "toggles", "items": [{"title": "Type annotations", "body": "<code>local x: number = 5</code> — gradual, optional types enforced by the checker.", "open": true}, {"title": "Generalized iteration", "body": "<code>for k, v in t do</code> — no need for pairs()/ipairs()."}, {"title": "String interpolation", "body": "Backtick strings: <code>`Hello, {name}!`</code> with embedded expressions."}, {"title": "Continue statement", "body": "<code>continue</code> inside loops skips to the next iteration."}, {"title": "Compound assignment", "body": "<code>+=, -=, *=, /=, //=, %=, ^=, ..=</code> operators."}, {"title": "If-then-else expressions", "body": "<code>local x = if cond then a else b</code> — true ternary."}, {"title": "Floor division //", "body": "<code>7 // 2 == 3</code>. Rounds toward negative infinity."}, {"title": "table.freeze / table.clone", "body": "Make tables immutable or shallow-copy them."}, {"title": "Buffer type", "body": "Fixed-size binary data for serialization and networking."}, {"title": "Native codegen", "body": "Hot functions compile to machine code for 2-5x speedups."}]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📖 Course Structure", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>40 in-depth lessons</strong> across 12 sections, each with code examples and quizzes:<br><br>• <strong>Fundamentals</strong> — Variables, operators, control flow, functions<br>• <strong>Data Structures</strong> — Tables, strings, metatables, OOP<br>• <strong>Advanced Luau</strong> — Types, modules, coroutines, error handling<br>• <strong>Standard Libraries</strong> — math, string, table, buffer, bit32, os<br>• <strong>Roblox Core</strong> — Instances, services, events, client-server, datastores<br>• <strong>Roblox Advanced</strong> — Tweens, input, raycasting, GUI, parallel Luau, performance<br>• <strong>Debugging & Testing</strong> — Debug techniques, MicroProfiler, unit testing<br>• <strong>Capstone</strong> — Build a complete game system from scratch"}]}], "quiz": null}, {"id": 1, "title": "Variables & Types", "icon": "📦", "color": "#00d4ff", "desc": "The building blocks of every Luau script", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🧠 What Are Variables?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Imagine you have a bunch of labeled boxes. You write a name on each box, then put something inside. That's exactly what a <strong>variable</strong> is — a <strong>named container</strong> that holds a value."}, {"type": "text", "value": "For example, if you're making a game, you might need to keep track of a player's name, their health, and whether they're alive. You'd create three variables:"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local playerName = \"Zeeval\"    -- a box labeled 'playerName' containing the text \"Zeeval\"\nlocal health = 100             -- a box labeled 'health' containing the number 100\nlocal isAlive = true           -- a box labeled 'isAlive' containing true (yes)"}, {"type": "text", "value": "Let's break that down piece by piece:"}, {"type": "text", "value": "• <code>local</code> — This keyword tells Luau: \"I'm creating a new variable.\" You'll type this <em>every</em> time you make a variable.<br>• <code>playerName</code> — This is the <strong>name</strong> you're giving the variable. You choose it! It can be almost anything (letters, numbers, underscores — but must start with a letter).<br>• <code>=</code> — The equals sign means \"put this value inside.\" It does NOT mean \"is equal to\" here — it means <strong>assignment</strong> (storing a value).<br>• <code>\"Zeeval\"</code> — This is the <strong>value</strong> you're storing. Text goes in quotes. Numbers don't need quotes."}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Always Use 'local'", "text": "Get into the habit of <em>always</em> writing <code>local</code> before your variable names. Without it, the variable becomes \"global\" (accessible everywhere), which is slower and can cause confusing bugs. Think of <code>local</code> as best practice — you'll see it in every professional Roblox script."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "✏️ Your First Variables", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Try this in a Script in Roblox Studio. Type it out (don't just copy-paste — typing helps you learn!):"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Lines starting with -- are \"comments\"\n-- The computer ignores them. They're notes for YOU.\n\n-- Create some variables\nlocal myName = \"Alex\"\nlocal myAge = 14\nlocal isCool = true\n\n-- Print them to the Output window\nprint(myName)       -- shows: Alex\nprint(myAge)        -- shows: 14\nprint(isCool)       -- shows: true\n\n-- You can change a variable's value later\nmyAge = 15          -- notice: NO 'local' here — the variable already exists\nprint(myAge)        -- shows: 15\n\n-- You can use variables together\nlocal greeting = \"Hello, my name is \" .. myName\nprint(greeting)     -- shows: Hello, my name is Alex"}, {"type": "text", "value": "Notice the <code>..</code> in the last example? That's how you <strong>join two pieces of text together</strong> in Luau. It's called <strong>concatenation</strong>. We'll cover this more later — for now just know that <code>..</code> glues text together."}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "What Happens If You Don't Assign a Value?", "text": "If you write <code>local x</code> without giving it a value, it automatically holds <code>nil</code> — which means \"nothing\" or \"empty.\" Think of it as an empty box."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📦 Types of Values (Data Types)", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Not all values are the same <em>kind</em> of thing. A number is different from a piece of text, which is different from true/false. In programming, we call these different kinds <strong>data types</strong>. Here are the ones you'll use most:"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong style='color:var(--accent)'>The Big 5 (you'll use these constantly):</strong>"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Type", "What It Is", "Examples"], "rows": [["nil", "Nothing / empty / no value", "nil"], ["boolean", "True or false (yes or no)", "true, false"], ["number", "Any number (whole or decimal)", "42, 3.14, -7, 0"], ["string", "Text (always in quotes)", "\"hello\", 'world', `hi`"], ["table", "A collection (list or dictionary)", "{1, 2, 3}, {name = \"Alex\"}"]]}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong style='color:var(--accent)'>Advanced types (you'll learn these later):</strong>"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Type", "What It Is", "When You'll See It"], "rows": [["function", "A reusable block of code", "Lesson 4"], ["thread", "A coroutine (paused code)", "Lesson 11"], ["userdata", "Roblox engine objects like Vector3, CFrame", "Lesson 16"], ["buffer", "Raw binary data (advanced)", "Lesson 15"]]}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- You can check what type a value is:\nprint(type(42))         -- \"number\"\nprint(type(\"hello\"))    -- \"string\"\nprint(type(true))       -- \"boolean\"\nprint(type(nil))        -- \"nil\"\nprint(type({1, 2, 3}))  -- \"table\""}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔢 Numbers in Detail", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Numbers in Luau are straightforward — they work just like you'd expect. You can write them in several formats:"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local whole = 255            -- a regular whole number\nlocal decimal = 3.14159      -- a decimal number\nlocal negative = -42         -- negative numbers work fine\nlocal big = 1_000_000        -- underscores for readability (still = 1000000)\nlocal sci = 1e6              -- scientific notation (= 1000000)\n\n-- These are less common but good to know:\nlocal hex = 0xFF             -- hexadecimal (= 255)\nlocal binary = 0b11111111    -- binary (= 255)\n\n-- Special values\nlocal infinity = math.huge   -- infinity\nlocal notANumber = 0/0       -- NaN (not a number)\nprint(notANumber == notANumber) -- false! NaN never equals itself (weird but true)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📝 Strings (Text) in Detail", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "A <strong>string</strong> is just text. You put it inside quotes so Luau knows it's text and not code. There are several ways to write strings:"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Double quotes (most common)\nlocal greeting = \"Hello, World!\"\n\n-- Single quotes (same thing, just different quotes)\nlocal greeting2 = 'Hello, World!'\n\n-- Backticks — THE COOL ONE: lets you insert variables directly!\nlocal name = \"Alex\"\nlocal message = `Hello, {name}! Welcome to my game.`\nprint(message)  -- \"Hello, Alex! Welcome to my game.\"\n\n-- Backtick strings can even do math inside {}:\nlocal score = 50\nlocal display = `Score: {score * 2}`  -- \"Score: 100\"\n\n-- Joining strings with .. (concatenation)\nlocal first = \"Hello\"\nlocal second = \"World\"\nlocal combined = first .. \" \" .. second  -- \"Hello World\""}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Backticks vs Quotes", "text": "Use <strong>backticks (`)</strong> when you want to insert variables into text — it's cleaner than joining with <code>..</code>. Use regular <strong>quotes (\" or ')</strong> for simple text that doesn't need variable insertion."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏷️ Type Annotations (Optional but Helpful)", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Luau lets you add <strong>type annotations</strong> — labels that say what type of value a variable should hold. These are completely <strong>optional</strong>, but they help catch bugs and make your code clearer:"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Without type annotations (totally fine!):\nlocal name = \"Zeeval\"\nlocal score = 100\nlocal alive = true\n\n-- With type annotations (adds clarity):\nlocal name: string = \"Zeeval\"\nlocal score: number = 100\nlocal alive: boolean = true\n\n-- The type goes after the variable name, separated by a colon.\n-- If you accidentally put the wrong type, Luau will warn you in Studio."}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "type() vs typeof()", "text": "<code>type(v)</code> returns the basic Lua type (number, string, table, etc.). <code>typeof(v)</code> is Roblox-specific and also returns special types like \"Instance\", \"Vector3\", \"Color3\", etc. In Roblox, prefer <code>typeof()</code>."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚠️ Common Beginner Gotchas", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Here are mistakes that trip up <em>every</em> beginner. Knowing them now saves you hours of frustration:"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>1. Truthiness is different in Luau!</strong><br>If you've used other languages: in Luau, <code>0</code> is <strong>truthy</strong> (considered \"true\") and empty string <code>\"\"</code> is also <strong>truthy</strong>. Only <code>false</code> and <code>nil</code> are considered \"false\". This is different from JavaScript and Python!"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>2. = is not ==</strong><br>One equals sign <code>=</code> means \"store this value\" (assignment). Two equals signs <code>==</code> means \"check if these are equal\" (comparison). Mixing them up is the #1 beginner bug."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local x = 5      -- ASSIGNS the value 5 to x\nprint(x == 5)    -- CHECKS if x equals 5 → true\nprint(x == 10)   -- CHECKS if x equals 10 → false"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>3. Strings are immutable</strong><br>You can't change a string after creating it. Operations like <code>string.upper()</code> return a <em>new</em> string — the original stays the same."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What is the value of <code>local x</code> (declared but not assigned)?", "options": [{"text": "0", "correct": false}, {"text": "false", "correct": false}, {"text": "nil", "correct": true}, {"text": "undefined", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Unassigned variables default to <code>nil</code>.", "incorrect": "In Luau, all unassigned variables are <code>nil</code>."}}, {"id": 2, "title": "Operators", "icon": "⚙️", "color": "#ff79c6", "desc": "Arithmetic, relational, logical, and Luau-specific operators", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🧮 What Are Operators?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "An <strong>operator</strong> is a symbol that tells the computer to do something with values. You already know some operators from math class: <code>+</code> adds numbers, <code>-</code> subtracts them. Programming has all those <em>plus</em> some extras."}, {"type": "text", "value": "Think of operators as <strong>verbs</strong> — they perform <em>actions</em> on your data. <code>5 + 3</code> tells the computer \"add 5 and 3.\" <code>score > 100</code> tells it \"check if score is bigger than 100.\""}, {"type": "text", "value": "There are four main categories: <strong>arithmetic</strong> (math), <strong>comparison</strong> (checking values), <strong>logical</strong> (and/or/not), and <strong>string</strong> (text operations). Let's go through each one."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "➕ Arithmetic Operators", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Operator", "Name", "Example", "Result"], "rows": [["+", "Addition", "5 + 3", "8"], ["-", "Subtraction", "5 - 3", "2"], ["*", "Multiplication", "5 * 3", "15"], ["/", "Division", "7 / 2", "3.5"], ["//", "Floor division (Luau)", "7 // 2", "3"], ["%", "Modulo", "7 % 3", "1"], ["^", "Exponentiation", "2 ^ 10", "1024"], ["-x", "Unary minus", "-5", "-5"]]}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Luau Exclusive", "text": "<code>//</code> floor division is Luau-only. It rounds toward negative infinity: <code>-7 // 2 == -4</code>."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔄 Compound Assignment (Luau Only)", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local x = 10\nx += 5    -- x = x + 5  → 15\nx -= 3    -- x = x - 3  → 12\nx *= 2    -- x = x * 2  → 24\nx /= 4    -- x = x / 4  → 6\nx //= 2   -- x = x // 2 → 3\nx %= 2    -- x = x % 2  → 1\n\nlocal s = \"Hello\"\ns ..= \" World\"  -- concatenation assignment"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔁 Relational & Logical", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Relational operators</strong> compare two values and return <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>. You use these in <code>if</code> statements (next lesson!) to make decisions. <strong>Logical operators</strong> (<code>and</code>, <code>or</code>, <code>not</code>) combine conditions together."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Relational (return boolean)\n5 == 5    -- true (equality)\n5 ~= 3    -- true (NOT EQUAL — Lua uses ~= not !=)\n5 > 3     -- true\n5 >= 5    -- true\n\n-- Logical: and, or, not (return operands!)\nnil or \"default\"     -- \"default\"\n\"hi\" or \"fallback\"   -- \"hi\" (short-circuits)\n5 and 10             -- 10\nfalse and 10         -- false\nnot true             -- false\n\n-- Default value pattern\nlocal speed = playerSpeed or 16"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "No != Operator", "text": "Lua uses <code>~=</code> for \"not equal\", not <code>!=</code>. This trips up developers from C/JS/Python backgrounds."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔗 String & Length", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Concatenation (..)\nlocal s = \"Hello\" .. \" World\"  -- \"Hello World\"\n\n-- Length (#)\n#\"Hello\"           -- 5\n#{10, 20, 30}      -- 3\n\n-- WARNING: # on tables with nil holes is undefined!\nlocal gapped = {1, nil, 3}\nprint(#gapped)  -- could be 1 or 3 (don't rely on this)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>7 // 2</code> evaluate to in Luau?", "options": [{"text": "3.5", "correct": false}, {"text": "3", "correct": true}, {"text": "4", "correct": false}, {"text": "Error", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>//</code> is floor division: 7 ÷ 2 = 3.5, floored to 3.", "incorrect": "<code>//</code> is Luau's floor division. 7 // 2 = 3."}}, {"id": 3, "title": "Control Flow", "icon": "🔀", "color": "#50fa7b", "desc": "if/else, loops, break, continue, and iteration", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🤔 Making Decisions in Code", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "So far, your code runs from top to bottom, line by line. But real games need to make <strong>decisions</strong>: Is the player's health zero? Did they press a button? Do they have enough coins?"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Control flow</strong> is how you tell the computer: \"do this <em>if</em> something is true\" or \"keep doing this <em>while</em> a condition holds\" or \"do this 10 <em>times</em>.\" It's the difference between a dumb script that does the same thing every time and a smart game that reacts to the player."}, {"type": "text", "value": "Think of it like a <strong>choose-your-own-adventure book</strong>: \"If you open the door, go to page 5. If you run away, go to page 12.\" Code works the same way — except instead of pages, you have blocks of code."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔀 if / elseif / else", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "The <code>if</code> statement is the most fundamental decision-maker. It checks a condition — if the condition is <strong>true</strong>, the code inside runs. If not, it's skipped. You can chain conditions with <code>elseif</code> and provide a fallback with <code>else</code>."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local hp = 45\n\nif hp <= 0 then\n    print(\"Dead\")\nelseif hp < 25 then\n    print(\"Critical!\")\nelseif hp < 50 then\n    print(\"Low health\")    -- ← runs\nelse\n    print(\"Healthy\")\nend\n\n-- Luau if-expression (true ternary!)\nlocal label = if hp > 50 then \"healthy\" else \"wounded\"\nlocal abs = if hp < 0 then -hp else hp"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Luau If-Expression", "text": "<code>if cond then a else b</code> as an expression is Luau-only. Safer than the <code>and/or</code> trick — works even when the true-branch is <code>false</code> or <code>nil</code>."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔁 Loops", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "A <strong>loop</strong> repeats a block of code. Instead of writing <code>print(1) print(2) print(3)...</code> ten times, you write one loop and it does the work for you. There are several types — expand each one below to see how it works."}, {"type": "toggles", "items": [{"title": "while loop", "body": "<pre>local i = 1\nwhile i <= 5 do\n    print(i)\n    i += 1\nend</pre>", "open": true}, {"title": "repeat...until (runs at least once)", "body": "<pre>local n = 0\nrepeat\n    n += 1\nuntil n >= 5\nprint(n)  -- 5</pre>"}, {"title": "Numeric for", "body": "<pre>for i = 1, 10 do print(i) end\nfor i = 10, 1, -2 do print(i) end  -- 10,8,6,4,2</pre>"}, {"title": "Generic for (ipairs/pairs)", "body": "<pre>local t = {\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"}\nfor i, v in ipairs(t) do print(i, v) end\n\nlocal d = {x=1, y=2}\nfor k, v in pairs(d) do print(k, v) end\n\n-- Luau: no pairs/ipairs needed!\nfor k, v in d do print(k, v) end</pre>"}]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⏭ break & continue", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "for i = 1, 10 do\n    if i % 2 == 0 then\n        continue   -- skip even numbers (Luau only!)\n    end\n    if i > 7 then\n        break      -- stop at 7\n    end\n    print(i)       -- 1, 3, 5, 7\nend\n\n-- Real-world: skip invalid entries\nfor _, player in game.Players:GetPlayers() do\n    if not player.Character then continue end\n    local humanoid = player.Character:FindFirstChild(\"Humanoid\")\n    if not humanoid then continue end\n    humanoid.Health = 100\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Luau Exclusive", "text": "<code>continue</code> doesn't exist in standard Lua 5.1. It greatly reduces nesting compared to chained if/else blocks."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "Which loop runs its body at least once?", "options": [{"text": "while", "correct": false}, {"text": "numeric for", "correct": false}, {"text": "repeat...until", "correct": true}, {"text": "generic for", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>repeat...until</code> checks after the body runs.", "incorrect": "<code>repeat...until</code> checks after running — it always executes at least once."}}, {"id": 4, "title": "Functions & Closures", "icon": "🔧", "color": "#ffd93d", "desc": "First-class functions, closures, varargs, and methods", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🧩 What Are Functions?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Imagine you're making a sandwich. You do the same steps every time: get bread, add filling, close it up. Now imagine you could <strong>name</strong> those steps — \"makeSandwich\" — and just say that name whenever you want a sandwich, instead of repeating every step."}, {"type": "text", "value": "That's a <strong>function</strong>. It's a <strong>reusable block of code</strong> that you give a name to. You write the steps once, then \"call\" (use) the function whenever you need it. Functions can also take <strong>inputs</strong> (called <em>parameters</em>) and give back <strong>outputs</strong> (called <em>return values</em>)."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Define a simple function\nlocal function sayHello()\n    print(\"Hello there!\")\nend\n\n-- \"Call\" (use) it — this runs the code inside\nsayHello()  -- prints: Hello there!\nsayHello()  -- prints: Hello there! (again!)\n\n-- A function with an INPUT (parameter)\nlocal function greet(name)\n    print(\"Hello, \" .. name .. \"!\")\nend\n\ngreet(\"Alex\")    -- prints: Hello, Alex!\ngreet(\"Jordan\")  -- prints: Hello, Jordan!\n\n-- A function with an OUTPUT (return value)\nlocal function add(a, b)\n    return a + b    -- sends the result back\nend\n\nlocal result = add(3, 7)  -- result = 10\nprint(result)             -- prints: 10"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Why Functions Matter", "text": "Functions are the <strong>single most important concept</strong> in programming. They let you organize code, avoid repetition, and build complex systems from small, testable pieces. Every Roblox game is built from hundreds of functions working together."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📌 Function Declarations", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Named (preferred — allows recursion)\nlocal function greet(name: string): string\n    return `Hello, {name}!`\nend\n\n-- Anonymous / expression form\nlocal add = function(a: number, b: number): number\n    return a + b\nend\n\n-- Multiple return values\nlocal function minMax(a, b)\n    if a < b then return a, b end\n    return b, a\nend\nlocal lo, hi = minMax(8, 3)  -- lo=3, hi=8\n\n-- Ignore returns with _\nlocal _, max = minMax(1, 5)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📦 Varargs & Defaults", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Variadic arguments\nlocal function sum(...: number): number\n    local total = 0\n    for _, v in {...} do total += v end\n    return total\nend\nprint(sum(1, 2, 3, 4))  -- 10\n\n-- select() for varargs\nprint(select(\"#\", 1, 2, 3))  -- 3 (count)\nprint(select(2, \"a\", \"b\", \"c\"))  -- \"b\", \"c\"\n\n-- Default parameter pattern\nlocal function spawn(name, hp, speed)\n    name = name or \"Zombie\"\n    hp = hp or 100\n    speed = speed or 16\n    -- ...\nend\n\n-- SAFER with if-expression (handles false correctly)\nlocal function setFlag(value: boolean?)\n    local v = if value ~= nil then value else true\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔒 Closures", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "A <strong>closure</strong> captures variables from its enclosing scope (<strong>upvalues</strong>). Each closure gets its own copy of the captured variables."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local function makeCounter(start: number)\n    local count = start  -- upvalue\n    return function()\n        count += 1\n        return count\n    end\nend\n\nlocal c = makeCounter(0)\nprint(c())  -- 1\nprint(c())  -- 2\nprint(c())  -- 3\n\n-- Practical: debounce\nlocal function debounce(fn, cooldown)\n    local lastCall = 0\n    return function(...)\n        local now = tick()\n        if now - lastCall >= cooldown then\n            lastCall = now\n            return fn(...)\n        end\n    end\nend\nlocal safeShoot = debounce(shoot, 0.5)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📐 Methods: Colon vs Dot", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local obj = { name = \"Hero\" }\n\n-- DOT: must pass self manually\nfunction obj.greet(self)\n    print(\"I am \" .. self.name)\nend\nobj.greet(obj)\n\n-- COLON: self is implicit (preferred for methods)\nfunction obj:greet2()\n    print(\"I am \" .. self.name)\nend\nobj:greet2()  -- self = obj automatically\n\n-- Equivalent: obj:method(a) == obj.method(obj, a)\n-- Use : for methods, . for static/utility functions"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "Common Bug", "text": "Calling <code>obj.method()</code> instead of <code>obj:method()</code> passes no self — you'll get nil errors on <code>self.anything</code>."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚡ Higher-Order Functions", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Map\nlocal function map(t, fn)\n    local r = {}\n    for i, v in t do r[i] = fn(v) end\n    return r\nend\nmap({1,2,3}, function(x) return x * 2 end)  -- {2,4,6}\n\n-- Filter\nlocal function filter(t, pred)\n    local r = {}\n    for _, v in t do\n        if pred(v) then table.insert(r, v) end\n    end\n    return r\nend\nfilter({1,2,3,4,5}, function(x) return x % 2 == 0 end) -- {2,4}\n\n-- Reduce\nlocal function reduce(t, fn, init)\n    local acc = init\n    for _, v in t do acc = fn(acc, v) end\n    return acc\nend\nreduce({1,2,3,4}, function(a,b) return a+b end, 0) -- 10"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>:</code> do when calling a function?", "options": [{"text": "Makes it private", "correct": false}, {"text": "Passes the table as first argument (self)", "correct": true}, {"text": "Makes it faster", "correct": false}, {"text": "Creates a new instance", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>obj:method(a)</code> = <code>obj.method(obj, a)</code>.", "incorrect": "The <code>:</code> syntax passes the table as <code>self</code> — purely syntactic sugar."}}, {"id": 5, "title": "Tables Deep Dive", "icon": "📋", "color": "#c77dff", "desc": "Arrays, dictionaries, the table library, and patterns", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📊 Three Modes", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- 1. ARRAY (1-indexed!)\nlocal inv = {\"Sword\", \"Shield\", \"Potion\"}\nprint(inv[1])   -- \"Sword\" (NOT [0]!)\nprint(#inv)     -- 3\n\n-- 2. DICTIONARY\nlocal player = {\n    name  = \"Zeeval\",\n    level = 25,\n    alive = true,\n}\nprint(player.name)       -- \"Zeeval\"\nprint(player[\"level\"])   -- 25\n\n-- 3. MIXED\nlocal m = {\"a\", \"b\", x = 10, \"c\"}\n-- Array: [1]=\"a\",[2]=\"b\",[3]=\"c\"  Dict: x=10\n-- #m == 3 (only counts array part)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🛠 table Library Reference", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Function", "Description"], "rows": [["table.insert(t, v)", "Append to end"], ["table.insert(t, i, v)", "Insert at index i"], ["table.remove(t [, i])", "Remove at i (default: last)"], ["table.sort(t [, comp])", "Sort in-place"], ["table.concat(t [, sep])", "Join array as string"], ["table.move(a1,f,e,t [,a2])", "Copy elements"], ["table.pack(...)", "Pack varargs ({...} with .n)"], ["table.unpack(t [,i,j])", "Return elements as values"], ["table.find(t, v [, init])", "Find index of value (Luau)"], ["table.clear(t)", "Remove all elements (Luau)"], ["table.freeze(t)", "Make read-only (Luau)"], ["table.isfrozen(t)", "Check if frozen (Luau)"], ["table.clone(t)", "Shallow copy (Luau)"], ["table.create(n [, v])", "Pre-allocate array (Luau)"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚡ Common Patterns", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Set pattern (O(1) lookup)\nlocal allowed = { Sword = true, Bow = true }\nif allowed[\"Sword\"] then print(\"OK\") end\n\n-- Stack (LIFO)\nlocal stack = {}\ntable.insert(stack, \"a\")  -- push\ntable.remove(stack)       -- pop\n\n-- Sort by property\nlocal items = {{n=\"Bow\",d=20},{n=\"Sword\",d=30}}\ntable.sort(items, function(a,b) return a.d > b.d end)\n\n-- Deep copy\nlocal function deepCopy(t)\n    if type(t) ~= \"table\" then return t end\n    local c = {}\n    for k, v in t do c[deepCopy(k)] = deepCopy(v) end\n    return setmetatable(c, getmetatable(t))\nend\n\n-- Immutable config\nlocal CONFIG = table.freeze({\n    MAX_HP = 100,\n    SPEED = 16,\n})\n-- CONFIG.MAX_HP = 200  -- ERROR!\n\n-- Pre-allocate for performance\nlocal big = table.create(1000, 0)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "Luau arrays start at index...?", "options": [{"text": "0", "correct": false}, {"text": "1", "correct": true}, {"text": "-1", "correct": false}, {"text": "It depends", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Lua/Luau arrays are 1-indexed.", "incorrect": "Lua/Luau uses <strong>1-based indexing</strong>. <code>t[1]</code> is the first element."}}, {"id": 6, "title": "Strings & Patterns", "icon": "🔤", "color": "#f1fa8c", "desc": "String library, formatting, and Lua pattern matching", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📚 String Library", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Function", "Description"], "rows": [["string.len(s) / #s", "Length in bytes"], ["string.sub(s, i, j)", "Substring (1-indexed, inclusive)"], ["string.upper(s) / lower(s)", "Case conversion"], ["string.rep(s, n [, sep])", "Repeat n times"], ["string.reverse(s)", "Reverse"], ["string.byte(s [, i])", "Byte value at position"], ["string.char(n, ...)", "Bytes to string"], ["string.format(fmt, ...)", "Printf-style formatting"], ["string.find(s, pat)", "Find pattern, return indices"], ["string.match(s, pat)", "First capture matching pattern"], ["string.gmatch(s, pat)", "Iterator over all matches"], ["string.gsub(s, pat, repl)", "Global substitution"], ["string.split(s, sep)", "Split by separator (Luau only)"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎨 string.format", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "string.format(\"%d\", 42)           -- \"42\"\nstring.format(\"%05d\", 7)          -- \"00007\"\nstring.format(\"%.2f\", 3.14159)    -- \"3.14\"\nstring.format(\"%s\", \"hello\")      -- \"hello\"\nstring.format(\"%q\", 'say \"hi\"')  -- '\"say \\\\\"hi\\\\\"\"'\nstring.format(\"%x\", 255)          -- \"ff\"\nstring.format(\"%%\")               -- \"%\"\n\n-- Timer display\nlocal function formatTime(sec)\n    return string.format(\"%02d:%02d\", sec // 60, sec % 60)\nend\nprint(formatTime(125))  -- \"02:05\""}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔍 Lua Patterns", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Lua patterns are NOT regex — they're simpler but cover most use cases."}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Pattern", "Matches"], "rows": [["%d", "Digit (0-9)"], ["%a", "Letter"], ["%l / %u", "Lower / upper"], ["%s", "Whitespace"], ["%w", "Alphanumeric"], ["%p", "Punctuation"], [".", "Any character"], ["*", "0+ (greedy)"], ["+", "1+ (greedy)"], ["-", "0+ (lazy)"], ["?", "Optional"], ["^", "Start anchor"], ["$", "End anchor"], ["()", "Capture group"], ["%bxy", "Balanced match"]]}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local s = \"Player_42 scored 150 pts\"\n\nstring.match(s, \"%d+\")      -- \"42\" (first number)\n\nfor n in string.gmatch(s, \"%d+\") do\n    print(n)  -- \"42\", \"150\"\nend\n\n-- Captures\nlocal name, id = string.match(\"Player_42\", \"(%a+)_(%d+)\")\n-- name=\"Player\", id=\"42\"\n\n-- Replace\nstring.gsub(s, \"%d+\", \"X\")  -- \"Player_X scored X pts\"\n\n-- string.split (Luau only)\nstring.split(\"a,b,c\", \",\")  -- {\"a\",\"b\",\"c\"}\n\n-- Method syntax works too\ns:upper()  s:find(\"42\")  s:split(\" \")"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>string.match(\"Hello123\", \"%d+\")</code> return?", "options": [{"text": "\"Hello\"", "correct": false}, {"text": "\"123\"", "correct": true}, {"text": "true", "correct": false}, {"text": "6", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>%d+</code> matches digits → \"123\".", "incorrect": "<code>%d+</code> matches one or more digits — returns \"123\"."}}, {"id": 7, "title": "Metatables", "icon": "🧬", "color": "#ff79c6", "desc": "Control table behavior with metamethods", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🔑 Basics", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "A <strong>metatable</strong> defines special behavior for a table via <strong>metamethods</strong> (keys prefixed with <code>__</code>)."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local t = {}\nlocal mt = {\n    __index = function(tbl, key)\n        return \"default\"  -- fallback for missing keys\n    end\n}\nsetmetatable(t, mt)\n\nprint(t.anything)  -- \"default\" (key missing → __index)\nt.name = \"real\"\nprint(t.name)      -- \"real\" (key exists → no __index)\n\n-- __index as a TABLE (prototype chain)\nlocal defaults = { hp = 100, speed = 16 }\nmt.__index = defaults\nprint(t.hp)    -- 100 (from defaults)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📖 All Metamethods", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Metamethod", "Triggered By"], "rows": [["__index", "Read missing key (function or table)"], ["__newindex", "Write to missing key"], ["__call", "t() — call as function"], ["__tostring", "tostring(t)"], ["__len", "#t"], ["__concat", "t .. x"], ["__eq", "t == x"], ["__lt", "t < x"], ["__le", "t <= x"], ["__add", "+"], ["__sub", "-"], ["__mul", "*"], ["__div", "/"], ["__mod", "%"], ["__pow", "^"], ["__unm", "unary -"], ["__idiv", "// (Luau)"], ["__iter", "for..in (Luau)"], ["__metatable", "protect getmetatable/setmetatable"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🧮 Example: Vector2", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local Vec2 = {}\nVec2.__index = Vec2\n\nfunction Vec2.new(x: number, y: number)\n    return setmetatable({x=x, y=y}, Vec2)\nend\n\nfunction Vec2.__add(a, b)\n    return Vec2.new(a.x + b.x, a.y + b.y)\nend\n\nfunction Vec2.__tostring(v)\n    return string.format(\"(%g, %g)\", v.x, v.y)\nend\n\nfunction Vec2.__len(v)\n    return math.sqrt(v.x^2 + v.y^2)\nend\n\nfunction Vec2:dot(other)\n    return self.x * other.x + self.y * other.y\nend\n\nlocal a = Vec2.new(3, 4)\nlocal b = Vec2.new(1, 2)\nprint(tostring(a + b))  -- \"(4, 6)\"\nprint(#a)               -- 5 (magnitude)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "When is <code>__index</code> called?", "options": [{"text": "Every read", "correct": false}, {"text": "Only when the key doesn't exist", "correct": true}, {"text": "On writes", "correct": false}, {"text": "On creation", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>__index</code> only fires for <strong>missing</strong> keys.", "incorrect": "<code>__index</code> is only called when the key is NOT found in the table itself."}}, {"id": 8, "title": "OOP Patterns", "icon": "🏛️", "color": "#50fa7b", "desc": "Classes, inheritance, and encapsulation", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🏗️ The Class Pattern", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local Animal = {}\nAnimal.__index = Animal\n\nfunction Animal.new(name: string, sound: string)\n    local self = setmetatable({}, Animal)\n    self.name = name\n    self.sound = sound\n    self.hp = 100\n    return self\nend\n\nfunction Animal:speak()\n    print(`{self.name} says {self.sound}!`)\nend\n\nfunction Animal:takeDamage(amount: number)\n    self.hp = math.max(0, self.hp - amount)\nend\n\nfunction Animal:__tostring()\n    return `{self.name} (HP: {self.hp})`\nend\n\nlocal cat = Animal.new(\"Whiskers\", \"Meow\")\ncat:speak()  -- \"Whiskers says Meow!\""}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🧬 Inheritance", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local Dog = setmetatable({}, {__index = Animal})\nDog.__index = Dog\n\nfunction Dog.new(name: string)\n    local self = Animal.new(name, \"Woof\")\n    return setmetatable(self, Dog)\nend\n\nfunction Dog:fetch(item: string)\n    print(`{self.name} fetches the {item}!`)\nend\n\n-- Override parent method\nfunction Dog:speak()\n    print(`{self.name} barks: {self.sound}! {self.sound}!`)\nend\n\nlocal rex = Dog.new(\"Rex\")\nrex:speak()         -- overridden\nrex:fetch(\"ball\")   -- new method\nrex:takeDamage(20)  -- inherited from Animal"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Lookup Chain", "text": "rex.speak → Dog (found!) | rex.takeDamage → Dog (miss) → Animal (found!). This is prototype-based inheritance via <code>__index</code>."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎮 Roblox Module Pattern", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- In a ModuleScript\nlocal Weapon = {}\nWeapon.__index = Weapon\n\nexport type WeaponType = {\n    name: string,\n    damage: number,\n    fire: (self: WeaponType) -> boolean,\n}\n\nfunction Weapon.new(name, damage): WeaponType\n    return setmetatable({\n        name = name,\n        damage = damage,\n        _lastFire = 0,\n    }, Weapon) :: any\nend\n\nfunction Weapon:fire(): boolean\n    local now = tick()\n    if now - self._lastFire < 0.5 then return false end\n    self._lastFire = now\n    return true\nend\n\nreturn Weapon\n\n-- Usage: local Weapon = require(path)\n-- local sword = Weapon.new(\"Sword\", 30)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Convention", "text": "Classes in ModuleScripts, imported with <code>require()</code>. Constructor uses <code>.</code> (no self), methods use <code>:</code> (implicit self)."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "Why set <code>Animal.__index = Animal</code>?", "options": [{"text": "Prevent modification", "correct": false}, {"text": "Make it callable", "correct": false}, {"text": "So instances find methods in Animal", "correct": true}, {"text": "Convention only", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Instances look up missing keys in Animal via <code>__index</code>.", "incorrect": "<code>__index = Animal</code> lets instances share Animal's methods."}}, {"id": 9, "title": "Luau Type System", "icon": "🏷️", "color": "#8be9fd", "desc": "Gradual typing, generics, unions, and type inference", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📐 Basic Annotations", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local x: number = 5\nlocal s: string = \"hello\"\nlocal b: boolean = true\nlocal t: {number} = {1, 2, 3}        -- array of numbers\nlocal d: {[string]: number} = {a=1}  -- dictionary\n\n-- Function types\nlocal function add(a: number, b: number): number\n    return a + b\nend\n\n-- Multiple returns\nlocal function divide(a, b): (number, boolean)\n    if b == 0 then return 0, false end\n    return a / b, true\nend\n\n-- Optional parameter\nlocal function greet(name: string, title: string?)\n    print(`Hello, {title or \"Player\"} {name}!`)\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔀 Unions, Intersections & Literals", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Union: one of multiple types\nlocal id: number | string = 42\nid = \"abc\"  -- also valid\n\n-- Optional = T | nil\nlocal name: string? = nil\n\n-- Literal types\ntype Direction = \"north\" | \"south\" | \"east\" | \"west\"\n\n-- Intersection: must satisfy ALL\ntype Named = { name: string }\ntype Leveled = { level: number }\ntype Hero = Named & Leveled\n\n-- Type narrowing\nlocal function process(v: string | number)\n    if type(v) == \"string\" then\n        print(v:upper())  -- Luau knows it's string\n    else\n        print(v + 1)      -- Luau knows it's number\n    end\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🧩 Generics & Type Aliases", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Type aliases\ntype Point = { x: number, y: number }\ntype Callback = (msg: string) -> ()\n\n-- Generic function\nlocal function first<T>(arr: {T}): T?\n    return arr[1]\nend\nfirst({1,2,3})    -- T = number\nfirst({\"a\",\"b\"})  -- T = string\n\n-- Generic type\ntype Result<T, E> = \n    { ok: true, value: T } | \n    { ok: false, error: E }\n\n-- Export types from modules\nexport type Weapon = {\n    name: string,\n    damage: number,\n}\n\n-- Type casting\nlocal x = getValue() :: number\nlocal y = ambiguous :: any  -- escape hatch"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>string?</code> mean?", "options": [{"text": "Empty string", "correct": false}, {"text": "string | nil", "correct": true}, {"text": "Non-empty string", "correct": false}, {"text": "Required string", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>T?</code> = <code>T | nil</code> — the value is optional.", "incorrect": "<code>?</code> suffix means optional: <code>string?</code> = <code>string | nil</code>."}}, {"id": 10, "title": "Modules & Code Org", "icon": "📁", "color": "#ffb86c", "desc": "ModuleScripts, require(), and architecture", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📦 ModuleScripts", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Roblox has 3 script types: <strong>Script</strong> (server), <strong>LocalScript</strong> (client), <strong>ModuleScript</strong> (shared library). Modules run when first <code>require()</code>'d and the result is cached."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- ModuleScript: ReplicatedStorage/MathUtils\nlocal M = {}\n\nfunction M.lerp(a, b, t)\n    return a + (b - a) * t\nend\n\nfunction M.clamp(v, min, max)\n    return math.clamp(v, min, max)\nend\n\nreturn M  -- MUST return something!\n\n-- In any script:\nlocal MathUtils = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.MathUtils)\nprint(MathUtils.lerp(0, 100, 0.5))  -- 50"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Caching", "text": "<code>require()</code> caches the return value. The module runs only once — all scripts share the same instance."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏗️ Architecture", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "text", "code": "game\n├─ ServerScriptService/\n│  ├─ Server.server.lua     -- entry point\n│  └─ Services/             -- server-only modules\n├─ ReplicatedStorage/\n│  ├─ Shared/               -- shared modules\n│  │  ├─ Constants.lua\n│  │  └─ Types.lua\n│  ├─ Classes/              -- shared classes\n│  └─ Remotes/              -- RemoteEvents\n├─ StarterPlayerScripts/\n│  ├─ Client.client.lua     -- client entry\n│  └─ Controllers/          -- client modules\n└─ ServerStorage/\n   └─ Assets/               -- models, templates"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Placement", "text": "<strong>ReplicatedStorage</strong> = shared (both sides). <strong>ServerStorage</strong> = server-only. <strong>StarterPlayerScripts</strong> = client-only."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What happens on second <code>require()</code> call?", "options": [{"text": "Runs module again", "correct": false}, {"text": "Returns cached result", "correct": true}, {"text": "Throws error", "correct": false}, {"text": "Returns nil", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Module runs once, result is cached.", "incorrect": "<code>require()</code> caches — code runs once."}}, {"id": 11, "title": "Coroutines & Async", "icon": "⏸️", "color": "#ff6b6b", "desc": "Cooperative multitasking and the task library", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "⚙️ Coroutine Basics", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local function producer()\n    for i = 1, 3 do\n        coroutine.yield(i)  -- pause, send value\n    end\n    return \"done\"\nend\n\nlocal co = coroutine.create(producer)\nlocal ok, v = coroutine.resume(co)  -- v=1\nok, v = coroutine.resume(co)        -- v=2\nok, v = coroutine.resume(co)        -- v=3\nok, v = coroutine.resume(co)        -- v=\"done\"\n\n-- coroutine.wrap: simpler API\nlocal next = coroutine.wrap(producer)\nprint(next())  -- 1\nprint(next())  -- 2"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎮 task Library (USE THIS!)", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "In Roblox, <strong>always use <code>task</code></strong> instead of raw coroutines or deprecated <code>wait()/spawn()</code>."}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Function", "Description"], "rows": [["task.spawn(f, ...)", "Run immediately in new thread"], ["task.defer(f, ...)", "Run after current cycle"], ["task.delay(t, f, ...)", "Run after t seconds"], ["task.wait(t?)", "Yield for t seconds (precise)"], ["task.cancel(thread)", "Cancel scheduled thread"], ["task.synchronize()", "Resume on Heartbeat (parallel)"], ["task.desynchronize()", "Switch to parallel actor"]]}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- DEPRECATED → MODERN\n-- wait(2)    → task.wait(2)\n-- spawn(fn)  → task.spawn(fn)\n-- delay(2,f) → task.delay(2, f)\n\ntask.spawn(function()\n    task.wait(2)\n    print(\"2 seconds later!\")\nend)\nprint(\"Runs immediately!\")\n\n-- Cancel a delayed task\nlocal t = task.delay(10, function()\n    print(\"Won't run\")\nend)\ntask.cancel(t)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What replaces deprecated <code>wait()</code>?", "options": [{"text": "coroutine.yield()", "correct": false}, {"text": "task.wait()", "correct": true}, {"text": "os.clock()", "correct": false}, {"text": "Heartbeat:Wait()", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>task.wait()</code> is the modern replacement.", "incorrect": "Use <code>task.wait()</code> — it's the official replacement."}}, {"id": 12, "title": "Error Handling", "icon": "🚨", "color": "#ff6b6b", "desc": "pcall, xpcall, error, assert, and patterns", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🛡️ pcall & xpcall", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- pcall: protected call → (ok, result_or_error)\nlocal ok, result = pcall(function()\n    return 10 + 20\nend)\nprint(ok, result)  -- true, 30\n\nlocal ok2, err = pcall(function()\n    error(\"Something broke!\")\nend)\nprint(ok2, err)  -- false, \"...:Something broke!\"\n\n-- pcall with arguments\nlocal ok3, data = pcall(store.GetAsync, store, key)\n\n-- xpcall: with error handler\nlocal ok, msg = xpcall(riskyFn, function(err)\n    warn(\"ERROR:\", err)\n    warn(debug.traceback(nil, 2))\n    return err\nend)\n\n-- Retry pattern\nlocal function withRetry(fn, attempts, delay)\n    for i = 1, attempts do\n        local ok, r = pcall(fn)\n        if ok then return r end\n        if i < attempts then task.wait(delay) end\n    end\n    error(\"All attempts failed\")\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚠️ error() & assert()", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- error(message, level)\n-- level: 1=here, 2=caller, 0=no location\nlocal function divide(a, b)\n    if b == 0 then\n        error(\"Division by zero\", 2)  -- blame caller\n    end\n    return a / b\nend\n\n-- assert: error if falsy, return value if truthy\nlocal p = assert(\n    game.Players:FindFirstChild(name),\n    `Player '{name}' not found`\n)\n\n-- Error objects (tables!)\nerror({ code = 404, message = \"Not found\" })\n\nlocal ok, err = pcall(riskyFn)\nif not ok and type(err) == \"table\" then\n    print(err.code, err.message)\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "DataStore Rule", "text": "Always wrap DataStore calls in <code>pcall</code> — they can fail due to rate limits, network issues, or throttling."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does pcall return on error?", "options": [{"text": "nil", "correct": false}, {"text": "Error only", "correct": false}, {"text": "false, error_value", "correct": true}, {"text": "Re-throws", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>pcall</code> returns <code>false, error</code> on failure.", "incorrect": "<code>pcall</code> returns <code>false, error_value</code> on failure, <code>true, results</code> on success."}}, {"id": 13, "title": "math Library", "icon": "🔢", "color": "#bd93f9", "desc": "Complete math reference with Luau additions", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📊 Constants & Core", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Function", "Description"], "rows": [["math.pi", "π ≈ 3.14159..."], ["math.huge", "Infinity"], ["math.abs(x)", "Absolute value"], ["math.floor(x)", "Round down"], ["math.ceil(x)", "Round up"], ["math.round(x)", "Round to nearest (Luau)"], ["math.sqrt(x)", "Square root"], ["math.min(...)", "Minimum"], ["math.max(...)", "Maximum"], ["math.clamp(x,min,max)", "Clamp (Luau)"], ["math.sign(x)", "Returns -1, 0, or 1 (Luau)"], ["math.random([m,n])", "Random number"], ["math.randomseed(n)", "Seed RNG"], ["math.log(x [,base])", "Logarithm"], ["math.exp(x)", "e^x"], ["math.fmod(x,y)", "Float modulo"], ["math.modf(x)", "Integer + fractional parts"], ["math.sin/cos/tan(x)", "Trig (radians)"], ["math.asin/acos/atan(x)", "Inverse trig"], ["math.atan2(y,x)", "Two-arg arctangent"], ["math.rad(deg)", "Degrees to radians"], ["math.deg(rad)", "Radians to degrees"], ["math.noise(x[,y,z])", "Perlin noise (Luau/Roblox)"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚡ Common Game Math", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Clamping health\nlocal hp = math.clamp(rawHp, 0, MAX_HP)\n\n-- Lerp (linear interpolation)\nlocal function lerp(a, b, t)\n    return a + (b - a) * math.clamp(t, 0, 1)\nend\n\n-- Random in range (inclusive)\nlocal r = math.random(1, 100)\n\n-- Distance between points\nlocal function dist(x1, y1, x2, y2)\n    return math.sqrt((x2-x1)^2 + (y2-y1)^2)\nend\n\n-- Angle from one point to another\nlocal angle = math.atan2(dy, dx)\n\n-- Perlin noise for terrain (Roblox)\nfor x = 1, 100 do\n    local height = math.noise(x/20, 0, seed) * 50\nend\n\n-- Round to N decimals\nlocal function round(v, decimals)\n    local m = 10 ^ (decimals or 0)\n    return math.round(v * m) / m\nend\nprint(round(3.14159, 2))  -- 3.14"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>math.clamp(15, 0, 10)</code> return?", "options": [{"text": "15", "correct": false}, {"text": "10", "correct": true}, {"text": "0", "correct": false}, {"text": "5", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>clamp</code> restricts value to [min, max] → 10.", "incorrect": "<code>clamp(15, 0, 10)</code> = 10 (capped at max)."}}, {"id": 14, "title": "table & string Deep Dive", "icon": "📚", "color": "#50fa7b", "desc": "Advanced patterns, performance tips, and edge cases", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🔧 Advanced Table Patterns", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Weak tables (for caching without preventing GC)\nlocal cache = setmetatable({}, { __mode = \"v\" })\n-- Values can be garbage collected when no other refs exist\n\n-- table.move: efficient bulk operations\nlocal a = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}\nlocal b = {10, 20, 30}\ntable.move(b, 1, 3, 4, a)  -- a = {1,2,3,10,20,30,...}\n\n-- Nested freeze (deep freeze)\nlocal function deepFreeze(t)\n    table.freeze(t)\n    for _, v in t do\n        if type(v) == \"table\" and not table.isfrozen(v) then\n            deepFreeze(v)\n        end\n    end\n    return t\nend\n\n-- table.create for pre-allocation\nlocal grid = table.create(100)\nfor i = 1, 100 do\n    grid[i] = table.create(100, 0)  -- 100x100 grid of zeros\nend\n\n-- Counting occurrences\nlocal function countBy(arr)\n    local counts = {}\n    for _, v in arr do\n        counts[v] = (counts[v] or 0) + 1\n    end\n    return counts\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔤 Advanced String Techniques", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- String as bytes buffer\nlocal bytes = {string.byte(\"Hello\", 1, -1)}  -- {72,101,...}\nlocal rebuilt = string.char(table.unpack(bytes))  -- \"Hello\"\n\n-- Pattern: validate input\nlocal function isAlphanumeric(s)\n    return s:match(\"^%w+$\") ~= nil\nend\n\n-- Pattern: extract key=value pairs\nlocal config = \"name=John;age=30;role=admin\"\nfor k, v in config:gmatch(\"(%w+)=(%w+)\") do\n    print(k, v)  -- name John, age 30, role admin\nend\n\n-- gsub with function replacement\nlocal template = \"Hello {name}, you have {coins} coins\"\nlocal data = { name = \"Alex\", coins = \"42\" }\nlocal result = template:gsub(\"{(%w+)}\", function(key)\n    return data[key] or \"{\" .. key .. \"}\"\nend)\n-- \"Hello Alex, you have 42 coins\"\n\n-- Performance: use table.concat for building strings\nlocal parts = {}\nfor i = 1, 1000 do\n    table.insert(parts, tostring(i))\nend\nlocal bigStr = table.concat(parts, \",\")\n-- MUCH faster than repeated .. concatenation"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "For building large strings, what's fastest?", "options": [{"text": "Repeated .. concatenation", "correct": false}, {"text": "string.format in a loop", "correct": false}, {"text": "table.insert + table.concat", "correct": true}, {"text": "String interpolation", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Collect parts in a table, then <code>table.concat()</code> once.", "incorrect": "Repeated <code>..</code> creates many intermediate strings. Use <code>table.concat()</code>."}}, {"id": 15, "title": "buffer, bit32 & os", "icon": "🔧", "color": "#8be9fd", "desc": "Binary data, bitwise operations, and system libraries", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📦 buffer Library (Luau)", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Fixed-size binary data for efficient serialization and networking."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local b = buffer.create(16)  -- 16 bytes\n\nbuffer.writei32(b, 0, 42)       -- int32 at offset 0\nbuffer.writef32(b, 4, 3.14)     -- float32 at offset 4\nbuffer.writeu8(b, 8, 255)       -- uint8 at offset 8\nbuffer.writestring(b, 9, \"Hi\")  -- string at offset 9\n\nprint(buffer.readi32(b, 0))       -- 42\nprint(buffer.readf32(b, 4))       -- ~3.14\nprint(buffer.readu8(b, 8))        -- 255\nprint(buffer.readstring(b, 9, 2)) -- \"Hi\"\nprint(buffer.len(b))              -- 16\n\n-- Copy and convert\nlocal copy = buffer.create(buffer.len(b))\nbuffer.copy(copy, 0, b, 0, buffer.len(b))\nlocal str = buffer.tostring(b)\nlocal b2 = buffer.fromstring(str)"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Function", "Description"], "rows": [["buffer.create(size)", "Create buffer of size bytes"], ["buffer.len(b)", "Get size"], ["buffer.readi8/i16/i32(b,off)", "Read signed int"], ["buffer.readu8/u16/u32(b,off)", "Read unsigned int"], ["buffer.readf32/f64(b,off)", "Read float"], ["buffer.writei8/.../writef64", "Write values"], ["buffer.readstring(b,off,len)", "Read string"], ["buffer.writestring(b,off,s)", "Write string"], ["buffer.copy(dst,doff,src,soff,n)", "Copy bytes"], ["buffer.tostring(b)", "Convert to string"], ["buffer.fromstring(s)", "Create from string"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔢 bit32 Library", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Bitwise operations (32-bit unsigned integers)\nbit32.band(0xFF, 0x0F)      -- 0x0F (AND)\nbit32.bor(0xF0, 0x0F)       -- 0xFF (OR)\nbit32.bxor(0xFF, 0x0F)      -- 0xF0 (XOR)\nbit32.bnot(0)               -- 0xFFFFFFFF (NOT)\nbit32.lshift(1, 4)          -- 16 (left shift)\nbit32.rshift(16, 4)         -- 1 (right shift)\nbit32.arshift(-1, 1)        -- preserves sign bit\nbit32.lrotate(v, n)         -- rotate left\nbit32.rrotate(v, n)         -- rotate right\nbit32.btest(a, b)           -- true if band(a,b) ~= 0\nbit32.extract(v, field, w)  -- extract bits\nbit32.replace(v, r, f, w)  -- replace bits\nbit32.countlz(v)            -- leading zeros\nbit32.countrz(v)            -- trailing zeros\n\n-- Use case: flags/permissions\nlocal ADMIN = bit32.lshift(1, 0)   -- 1\nlocal MOD   = bit32.lshift(1, 1)   -- 2\nlocal VIP   = bit32.lshift(1, 2)   -- 4\n\nlocal perms = bit32.bor(ADMIN, VIP) -- 5\nprint(bit32.btest(perms, ADMIN))    -- true\nprint(bit32.btest(perms, MOD))      -- false"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⏰ os Library (Limited in Roblox)", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- os.time(): Unix timestamp (seconds)\nlocal now = os.time()  -- e.g., 1700000000\n\n-- os.date(): format timestamp\nos.date(\"%Y-%m-%d\")           -- \"2024-11-15\"\nos.date(\"%H:%M:%S\")           -- \"14:30:00\"\nos.date(\"%A, %B %d\")          -- \"Friday, November 15\"\nos.date(\"!*t\", now)            -- UTC table\n\n-- os.clock(): high-precision CPU time (for benchmarking)\nlocal start = os.clock()\n-- ... expensive operation ...\nlocal elapsed = os.clock() - start\nprint(string.format(\"Took %.4f seconds\", elapsed))\n\n-- os.difftime(t2, t1): difference in seconds\nlocal t1 = os.time()\ntask.wait(2)\nlocal diff = os.difftime(os.time(), t1)  -- ~2\n\n-- Roblox also has:\n-- tick()        — high-precision time (deprecated, use os.clock)\n-- time()        — game time since start\n-- workspace:GetServerTimeNow() — server UTC time\n-- DateTime.now() — Roblox DateTime object"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Roblox Restrictions", "text": "In Roblox, <code>os.execute</code>, <code>os.remove</code>, <code>os.rename</code>, <code>io.*</code>, and <code>loadfile</code> are <strong>disabled</strong> for security. Use DataStores for persistence and HttpService for HTTP requests."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>bit32.bor(0xF0, 0x0F)</code> return?", "options": [{"text": "0x00", "correct": false}, {"text": "0xFF", "correct": true}, {"text": "0xF0", "correct": false}, {"text": "0x0F", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! OR combines all set bits: 0xF0 | 0x0F = 0xFF.", "incorrect": "Bitwise OR: 11110000 | 00001111 = 11111111 = 0xFF."}}, {"id": 16, "title": "Instances & Services", "icon": "🏗️", "color": "#00d4ff", "desc": "Roblox object model, hierarchy, and core services", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🧱 Instance Basics", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Create\nlocal part = Instance.new(\"Part\")\npart.Name = \"Platform\"\npart.Size = Vector3.new(10, 1, 10)\npart.Position = Vector3.new(0, 5, 0)\npart.Anchored = true\npart.BrickColor = BrickColor.new(\"Bright blue\")\npart.Material = Enum.Material.Neon\npart.Parent = workspace  -- adds to game world\n\n-- Find children\nlocal child = part:FindFirstChild(\"Decal\")\nlocal wait = part:WaitForChild(\"Script\", 5)  -- 5s timeout\nlocal typed = part:FindFirstChildOfClass(\"Script\")\nlocal desc = part:FindFirstDescendant(\"Handle\")\nlocal all = part:GetChildren()         -- direct children\nlocal deep = part:GetDescendants()     -- all descendants\n\n-- Hierarchy\nprint(part.Parent)     -- workspace\nprint(part:GetFullName())  -- \"Workspace.Platform\"\nprint(part:IsA(\"BasePart\"))  -- true\nprint(part:IsDescendantOf(workspace))  -- true\n\n-- Destroy\npart:Destroy()  -- removes, disconnects events, nils parent\n\n-- Clone\nlocal copy = original:Clone()\ncopy.Parent = workspace"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🌐 Core Services Reference", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Always use GetService (type-safe, works if renamed)\nlocal Players          = game:GetService(\"Players\")\nlocal RS               = game:GetService(\"ReplicatedStorage\")\nlocal SSS              = game:GetService(\"ServerScriptService\")\nlocal SS               = game:GetService(\"ServerStorage\")\nlocal Workspace        = game:GetService(\"Workspace\") -- or: workspace\nlocal RunService       = game:GetService(\"RunService\")\nlocal TweenService     = game:GetService(\"TweenService\")\nlocal UIS              = game:GetService(\"UserInputService\")\nlocal DataStoreService = game:GetService(\"DataStoreService\")\nlocal HttpService      = game:GetService(\"HttpService\")\nlocal MarketplaceService = game:GetService(\"MarketplaceService\")\nlocal SoundService     = game:GetService(\"SoundService\")\nlocal Lighting         = game:GetService(\"Lighting\")\nlocal Teams            = game:GetService(\"Teams\")\nlocal Chat             = game:GetService(\"Chat\")\nlocal PathfindingService = game:GetService(\"PathfindingService\")\nlocal PhysicsService   = game:GetService(\"PhysicsService\")\nlocal CollectionService = game:GetService(\"CollectionService\")\nlocal ContextActionService = game:GetService(\"ContextActionService\")\nlocal StarterGui       = game:GetService(\"StarterGui\")\nlocal BadgeService     = game:GetService(\"BadgeService\")\nlocal MemoryStoreService = game:GetService(\"MemoryStoreService\")"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Server vs Client", "text": "<strong>Server-only:</strong> ServerStorage, ServerScriptService, DataStoreService (writing), BadgeService<br><strong>Client-only:</strong> UserInputService, StarterGui (local), ContextActionService<br><strong>Both:</strong> ReplicatedStorage, Workspace, RunService, Players"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎮 Roblox Data Types", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Type", "Constructor", "Usage"], "rows": [["Vector3", "Vector3.new(x,y,z)", "3D position, size, direction"], ["Vector2", "Vector2.new(x,y)", "2D GUI position, UV coordinates"], ["CFrame", "CFrame.new(pos) / .lookAt(from,to)", "Position + orientation (4x4 matrix)"], ["Color3", "Color3.fromRGB(r,g,b) / .fromHSV()", "Colors"], ["BrickColor", "BrickColor.new(\"Name\")", "Legacy Roblox colors"], ["UDim2", "UDim2.new(sx,ox,sy,oy)", "GUI sizing (scale + offset)"], ["UDim", "UDim.new(scale,offset)", "Single axis"], ["Rect", "Rect.new(x1,y1,x2,y2)", "2D rectangle"], ["Ray", "Ray.new(origin, direction)", "Legacy ray (use workspace:Raycast)"], ["NumberRange", "NumberRange.new(min,max)", "Range for particles etc."], ["NumberSequence", "NumberSequence.new({...})", "Sequence for particle properties"], ["ColorSequence", "ColorSequence.new({...})", "Sequence for color gradients"], ["Enum", "Enum.Material.Neon", "Engine enumerations"], ["TweenInfo", "TweenInfo.new(time,style,dir)", "Tween configuration"], ["OverlapParams", "OverlapParams.new()", "Spatial query filtering"], ["RaycastParams", "RaycastParams.new()", "Raycast filtering"]]}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>part:Destroy()</code> do?", "options": [{"text": "Hides the part", "correct": false}, {"text": "Removes it, disconnects events, nils parent", "correct": true}, {"text": "Only sets Parent to nil", "correct": false}, {"text": "Marks it for garbage collection", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>Destroy()</code> removes from hierarchy, disconnects all connections, and locks the instance.", "incorrect": "<code>Destroy()</code> fully removes the instance — it can't be reused."}}, {"id": 17, "title": "Events & Signals", "icon": "📡", "color": "#ffd93d", "desc": "RBXScriptSignal, connections, and event patterns", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📡 Event Basics", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local Players = game:GetService(\"Players\")\n\n-- Connect: fires callback every time\nlocal conn = Players.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\n    print(player.Name .. \" joined!\")\nend)\n\n-- Disconnect when done\nconn:Disconnect()\n\n-- Once: fires once then auto-disconnects\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Once(function(player)\n    print(\"First player: \" .. player.Name)\nend)\n\n-- Wait: yields until event fires, returns args\nlocal player = Players.PlayerAdded:Wait()\n\n-- RunService loops (game loop)\nlocal RunService = game:GetService(\"RunService\")\n\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function(dt)\n    -- Runs every frame AFTER physics (dt = delta time)\n    -- Use for: game logic, NPC AI, custom physics\nend)\n\nRunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function(dt)\n    -- Client only! Runs every frame BEFORE rendering\n    -- Use for: camera, first-person arms, UI updates\nend)\n\nRunService.Stepped:Connect(function(time, dt)\n    -- Runs every frame BEFORE physics\n    -- Use for: input processing, pre-physics setup\nend)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔗 Important Events", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Player lifecycle\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\n    player.CharacterAdded:Connect(function(char)\n        local humanoid = char:WaitForChild(\"Humanoid\")\n        humanoid.Died:Connect(function()\n            print(player.Name .. \" died\")\n        end)\n    end)\nend)\n\nPlayers.PlayerRemoving:Connect(function(player)\n    -- Save data here!\nend)\n\n-- Instance events\npart.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\n    local player = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(hit.Parent)\n    if player then print(player.Name .. \" touched!\") end\nend)\n\npart.TouchEnded:Connect(function(hit) end)\npart.ChildAdded:Connect(function(child) end)\npart.ChildRemoved:Connect(function(child) end)\npart:GetPropertyChangedSignal(\"Position\"):Connect(function()\n    print(\"Part moved!\")\nend)\n\n-- Attribute changes\npart:GetAttributeChangedSignal(\"Health\"):Connect(function()\n    print(\"Health changed to:\", part:GetAttribute(\"Health\"))\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "Memory Leaks", "text": "Always <code>:Disconnect()</code> connections when they're no longer needed. Connections to destroyed instances are auto-cleaned, but connections on persistent objects can leak. Store connections in a table and clean up."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏗️ Custom Events (BindableEvent)", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- BindableEvent: same-context communication\nlocal event = Instance.new(\"BindableEvent\")\n\nevent.Event:Connect(function(data)\n    print(\"Received:\", data)\nend)\n\nevent:Fire(\"hello\")  -- triggers all connected callbacks\nevent:Fire({score = 100})  -- can send any data\n\n-- Connection management pattern\nlocal connections = {}\n\nlocal function cleanup()\n    for _, conn in connections do\n        conn:Disconnect()\n    end\n    table.clear(connections)\nend\n\ntable.insert(connections, part.Touched:Connect(onTouch))\ntable.insert(connections, RunService.Heartbeat:Connect(update))\n\n-- Later: cleanup() to disconnect all"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>:Once()</code> do on an event?", "options": [{"text": "Fires the event once", "correct": false}, {"text": "Connects and auto-disconnects after first fire", "correct": true}, {"text": "Waits for the event", "correct": false}, {"text": "Checks if event fired", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>:Once()</code> connects a callback that automatically disconnects after being called once.", "incorrect": "<code>:Once()</code> connects a one-time callback — it auto-disconnects after firing."}}, {"id": 18, "title": "Client-Server Communication", "icon": "🔁", "color": "#c77dff", "desc": "RemoteEvents, RemoteFunctions, and security", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📡 RemoteEvent", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Create RemoteEvent in ReplicatedStorage\n\n-- ═══ SERVER ═══\nlocal event = game.ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild(\"MyEvent\")\n\n-- Receive from client (first arg is always the player)\nevent.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, action, data)\n    print(player.Name, action, data)\n    -- VALIDATE EVERYTHING from client!\n    if type(action) ~= \"string\" then return end\nend)\n\n-- Send to one client\nevent:FireClient(somePlayer, \"hello\", {score = 100})\n\n-- Send to all clients\nevent:FireAllClients(\"announcement\", \"Server restart!\")\n\n-- ═══ CLIENT ═══\nlocal event = game.ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild(\"MyEvent\")\n\n-- Send to server\nevent:FireServer(\"jump\", {height = 50})\n\n-- Receive from server\nevent.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(action, data)\n    print(\"From server:\", action)\nend)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📞 RemoteFunction", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- RemoteFunction: request → response pattern\n\n-- ═══ SERVER ═══\nlocal func = game.ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild(\"GetData\")\n\nfunc.OnServerInvoke = function(player, key)\n    -- Validate!\n    if type(key) ~= \"string\" then return nil end\n    return playerData[player.UserId][key]\nend\n\n-- ═══ CLIENT ═══\nlocal func = game.ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild(\"GetData\")\nlocal coins = func:InvokeServer(\"coins\")\nprint(\"I have\", coins, \"coins\")"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "danger", "title": "Security Rules", "text": "<strong>NEVER trust the client!</strong><br>• Always validate types and ranges of remote arguments<br>• Never let clients set their own health, speed, or currency<br>• Server is authoritative — client requests, server decides<br>• Rate-limit remote calls to prevent spam<br>• Don't use <code>OnClientInvoke</code> — it lets the server yield on client code"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔒 Security Patterns", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Rate limiting\nlocal lastFire = {}\nlocal COOLDOWN = 0.5\n\nevent.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, ...)\n    local now = tick()\n    if lastFire[player] and now - lastFire[player] < COOLDOWN then\n        return  -- rate limited\n    end\n    lastFire[player] = now\n    -- Process request...\nend)\n\n-- Type validation helper\nlocal function validate(value, expectedType)\n    return type(value) == expectedType\nend\n\n-- Server-side validation\nevent.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, action, amount)\n    if not validate(action, \"string\") then return end\n    if not validate(amount, \"number\") then return end\n    if amount < 0 or amount > 1000 then return end\n    if amount ~= math.floor(amount) then return end\n    -- Safe to process\nend)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "Who should be authoritative for game state?", "options": [{"text": "The client", "correct": false}, {"text": "The server", "correct": true}, {"text": "Both equally", "correct": false}, {"text": "Whoever processes first", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! The server is always authoritative. Clients request, servers validate and decide.", "incorrect": "The <strong>server</strong> must be authoritative. Never trust client data."}}, {"id": 19, "title": "DataStores", "icon": "💾", "color": "#00ffb3", "desc": "Persistent data, saving, loading, and best practices", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "💾 DataStore Basics", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local DSS = game:GetService(\"DataStoreService\")\nlocal store = DSS:GetDataStore(\"PlayerData_v1\")\n\n-- Save data (SERVER ONLY)\nlocal function saveData(player: Player, data: {})\n    local key = \"user_\" .. player.UserId\n    local ok, err = pcall(function()\n        store:SetAsync(key, data)\n    end)\n    if not ok then warn(\"Save failed:\", err) end\nend\n\n-- Load data\nlocal function loadData(player: Player)\n    local key = \"user_\" .. player.UserId\n    local ok, data = pcall(function()\n        return store:GetAsync(key)\n    end)\n    if ok then\n        return data or {coins = 0, level = 1, inventory = {}}\n    end\n    warn(\"Load failed:\", data)\n    return {coins = 0, level = 1, inventory = {}}\nend\n\n-- UpdateAsync (atomic read-modify-write, preferred!)\nlocal function addCoins(userId, amount)\n    local ok, err = pcall(function()\n        store:UpdateAsync(\"user_\" .. userId, function(old)\n            old = old or {coins = 0}\n            old.coins += amount\n            return old\n        end)\n    end)\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏗️ Complete Save System", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local Players = game:GetService(\"Players\")\nlocal DSS = game:GetService(\"DataStoreService\")\nlocal store = DSS:GetDataStore(\"GameData_v2\")\n\nlocal playerData = {}  -- cache in memory\n\nlocal DEFAULT_DATA = table.freeze({\n    coins = 0,\n    level = 1,\n    xp = 0,\n    inventory = {},\n    settings = { music = true, sfx = true },\n})\n\nlocal function deepCopy(t)\n    if type(t) ~= \"table\" then return t end\n    local c = {}\n    for k, v in t do c[k] = deepCopy(v) end\n    return c\nend\n\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\n    local data = loadData(player) -- from above\n    -- Merge with defaults (handles new fields)\n    local merged = deepCopy(DEFAULT_DATA)\n    for k, v in data do merged[k] = v end\n    playerData[player.UserId] = merged\nend)\n\nPlayers.PlayerRemoving:Connect(function(player)\n    local data = playerData[player.UserId]\n    if data then\n        saveData(player, data)\n        playerData[player.UserId] = nil\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Also save on shutdown!\ngame:BindToClose(function()\n    for _, player in Players:GetPlayers() do\n        local data = playerData[player.UserId]\n        if data then\n            pcall(store.SetAsync, store,\n                \"user_\" .. player.UserId, data)\n        end\n    end\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "DataStore Limits", "text": "• 60 + numPlayers × 10 requests/min per server<br>• 4MB max per key<br>• 50 chars max key length<br>• Always use pcall — requests can fail!<br>• Use <code>UpdateAsync</code> over <code>SetAsync</code> to prevent data races"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "Why use <code>UpdateAsync</code> over <code>SetAsync</code>?", "options": [{"text": "It's faster", "correct": false}, {"text": "Atomic read-modify-write prevents data races", "correct": true}, {"text": "It uses less quota", "correct": false}, {"text": "It auto-retries", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>UpdateAsync</code> reads the current value, lets you modify it, and writes atomically — preventing race conditions.", "incorrect": "<code>UpdateAsync</code> is atomic — it reads, modifies, and writes in one operation, preventing lost updates."}}, {"id": 20, "title": "TweenService & Animation", "icon": "✨", "color": "#ffd93d", "desc": "Smooth animations, easing styles, and tween patterns", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "✨ TweenService Basics", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local TweenService = game:GetService(\"TweenService\")\n\n-- TweenInfo(time, easingStyle, easingDirection, repeatCount, reverses, delayTime)\nlocal info = TweenInfo.new(\n    1,                          -- duration (seconds)\n    Enum.EasingStyle.Quad,      -- easing style\n    Enum.EasingDirection.Out,   -- direction\n    0,                          -- repeat (0 = no repeat, -1 = infinite)\n    false,                      -- reverse\n    0                           -- delay\n)\n\n-- Create tween\nlocal part = workspace.MyPart\nlocal tween = TweenService:Create(part, info, {\n    Position = Vector3.new(0, 20, 0),\n    Color = Color3.fromRGB(255, 0, 0),\n    Transparency = 0.5,\n})\n\ntween:Play()\ntween.Completed:Wait()  -- yield until done\nprint(\"Tween finished!\")\n\n-- Controls\ntween:Pause()\ntween:Cancel()  -- resets to original\ntween:Play()    -- resume from current\n\n-- Chain tweens\nlocal function tweenSequence(part)\n    local t1 = TweenService:Create(part, TweenInfo.new(1), {\n        Position = Vector3.new(0, 10, 0)\n    })\n    local t2 = TweenService:Create(part, TweenInfo.new(0.5), {\n        Size = Vector3.new(4, 4, 4)\n    })\n    t1:Play()\n    t1.Completed:Wait()\n    t2:Play()\n    t2.Completed:Wait()\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎨 Easing Styles", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Style", "Description"], "rows": [["Linear", "Constant speed"], ["Quad", "Quadratic (smooth)"], ["Cubic", "Cubic (smoother)"], ["Quart", "Quartic"], ["Quint", "Quintic"], ["Sine", "Sinusoidal (natural)"], ["Exponential", "Exponential"], ["Circular", "Circular arc"], ["Elastic", "Spring-like overshoot"], ["Back", "Slight overshoot"], ["Bounce", "Bouncing effect"]]}, {"type": "text", "value": "Each style combines with <strong>In</strong> (start slow), <strong>Out</strong> (end slow), or <strong>InOut</strong> (both) directions."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Useful tween patterns\n-- Fade in\nTweenService:Create(gui, TweenInfo.new(0.3), {\n    BackgroundTransparency = 0\n}):Play()\n\n-- Smooth camera shake\nlocal original = camera.CFrame\nfor i = 1, 5 do\n    local offset = Vector3.new(\n        math.random(-10, 10)/100,\n        math.random(-10, 10)/100,\n        0\n    )\n    TweenService:Create(camera, TweenInfo.new(0.05), {\n        CFrame = original * CFrame.new(offset)\n    }):Play()\n    task.wait(0.05)\nend\ncamera.CFrame = original"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>repeatCount = -1</code> do in TweenInfo?", "options": [{"text": "No repeat", "correct": false}, {"text": "Repeat once", "correct": false}, {"text": "Repeat infinitely", "correct": true}, {"text": "Error", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! -1 means infinite repetition.", "incorrect": "-1 = infinite repeat. 0 = no repeat. Positive = that many repeats."}}, {"id": 21, "title": "User Input & GUI", "icon": "🎮", "color": "#ff79c6", "desc": "UserInputService, ContextActionService, and GUI programming", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🎮 UserInputService", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local UIS = game:GetService(\"UserInputService\")\n\n-- Keyboard\nUIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(input, gameProcessed)\n    if gameProcessed then return end  -- ignore if typing in chat\n    if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.E then\n        print(\"E pressed!\")\n    end\n    if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.Space then\n        print(\"Jump!\")\n    end\nend)\n\nUIS.InputEnded:Connect(function(input, gameProcessed)\n    if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.E then\n        print(\"E released!\")\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Check if key is currently held\nif UIS:IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.LeftShift) then\n    print(\"Sprinting!\")\nend\n\n-- Mouse\nUIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(input)\n    if input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton1 then\n        print(\"Left click at\", input.Position)\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Mobile touch\nUIS.TouchStarted:Connect(function(touch, gameProcessed)\n    print(\"Touch at\", touch.Position)\nend)\n\n-- Device detection\nprint(UIS.TouchEnabled)     -- mobile/tablet\nprint(UIS.KeyboardEnabled)  -- PC\nprint(UIS.GamepadEnabled)   -- console"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🖥️ GUI Programming", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Create GUI from script (usually done in Studio)\nlocal player = game.Players.LocalPlayer\nlocal gui = player:WaitForChild(\"PlayerGui\")\n\nlocal screen = Instance.new(\"ScreenGui\")\nscreen.Parent = gui\n\nlocal frame = Instance.new(\"Frame\")\nframe.Size = UDim2.new(0, 200, 0, 100)  -- 200x100 pixels\nframe.Position = UDim2.new(0.5, -100, 0.5, -50)  -- centered\nframe.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(30, 30, 30)\nframe.Parent = screen\n\nlocal label = Instance.new(\"TextLabel\")\nlabel.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0.5, 0)  -- full width, half height\nlabel.Text = \"Hello World!\"\nlabel.TextColor3 = Color3.new(1, 1, 1)\nlabel.BackgroundTransparency = 1\nlabel.Font = Enum.Font.GothamBold\nlabel.TextSize = 24\nlabel.Parent = frame\n\nlocal button = Instance.new(\"TextButton\")\nbutton.Size = UDim2.new(1, -20, 0, 30)\nbutton.Position = UDim2.new(0, 10, 1, -40)\nbutton.Text = \"Click Me!\"\nbutton.Parent = frame\n\nbutton.MouseButton1Click:Connect(function()\n    label.Text = \"Clicked!\"\nend)\n\n-- UDim2 explained:\n-- UDim2.new(scaleX, offsetX, scaleY, offsetY)\n-- Scale: 0-1 relative to parent\n-- Offset: pixels\n-- UDim2.fromScale(0.5, 0.5) = center\n-- UDim2.fromOffset(100, 50) = 100x50 pixels"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>gameProcessed</code> mean in InputBegan?", "options": [{"text": "Input was processed by the game engine", "correct": false}, {"text": "Input was consumed by UI/chat (you should often ignore it)", "correct": true}, {"text": "The game is loading", "correct": false}, {"text": "Input came from a gamepad", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! If <code>gameProcessed</code> is true, a GUI element (like chat) already consumed the input.", "incorrect": "<code>gameProcessed = true</code> means a GUI/chat consumed the input — usually you should ignore it."}}, {"id": 22, "title": "Raycasting & Physics", "icon": "🎯", "color": "#ffb86c", "desc": "Raycasts, spatial queries, collision groups, and physics", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🎯 Raycasting", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Modern raycasting (workspace:Raycast)\nlocal origin = Vector3.new(0, 10, 0)\nlocal direction = Vector3.new(0, -100, 0)  -- down\n\n-- Basic raycast\nlocal result = workspace:Raycast(origin, direction)\nif result then\n    print(\"Hit:\", result.Instance.Name)\n    print(\"Position:\", result.Position)\n    print(\"Normal:\", result.Normal)  -- surface normal\n    print(\"Material:\", result.Material)\n    print(\"Distance:\", result.Distance)\nend\n\n-- With filtering\nlocal params = RaycastParams.new()\nparams.FilterType = Enum.RaycastFilterType.Exclude\nparams.FilterDescendantsInstances = {character}  -- ignore self\nparams.IgnoreWater = true\n\nlocal result = workspace:Raycast(origin, direction, params)\n\n-- Mouse to world raycast\nlocal camera = workspace.CurrentCamera\nlocal mouse = game.Players.LocalPlayer:GetMouse()\n\nlocal ray = camera:ViewportPointToRay(mouse.X, mouse.Y)\nlocal result = workspace:Raycast(\n    ray.Origin,\n    ray.Direction * 1000,\n    params\n)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📦 Spatial Queries", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Get parts in a region\nlocal params = OverlapParams.new()\nparams.FilterType = Enum.RaycastFilterType.Include\nparams.FilterDescendantsInstances = {workspace.Enemies}\n\n-- Box query\nlocal parts = workspace:GetPartBoundsInBox(\n    CFrame.new(0, 5, 0),    -- center\n    Vector3.new(10, 10, 10), -- size\n    params\n)\n\n-- Sphere query\nlocal parts = workspace:GetPartBoundsInRadius(\n    Vector3.new(0, 5, 0),  -- center\n    20,                     -- radius\n    params\n)\n\n-- For each hit part\nfor _, part in parts do\n    print(\"Found:\", part.Name)\nend\n\n-- Collision groups (PhysicsService)\nlocal PS = game:GetService(\"PhysicsService\")\nPS:RegisterCollisionGroup(\"Players\")\nPS:RegisterCollisionGroup(\"Projectiles\")\nPS:CollisionGroupSetCollidable(\"Players\", \"Projectiles\", false)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>workspace:Raycast</code> return on miss?", "options": [{"text": "false", "correct": false}, {"text": "Empty table", "correct": false}, {"text": "nil", "correct": true}, {"text": "Error", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Returns <code>nil</code> if the ray doesn't hit anything.", "incorrect": "<code>workspace:Raycast()</code> returns <code>nil</code> on miss, or a RaycastResult on hit."}}, {"id": 23, "title": "Parallel Luau & Performance", "icon": "⚡", "color": "#00d4ff", "desc": "Multi-threading, optimization, and best practices", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🧵 Parallel Luau", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Parallel Luau lets scripts run on multiple cores using <strong>Actors</strong>. Scripts inside an Actor can call <code>task.desynchronize()</code> to run in parallel."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Structure: Actor → Script inside it\n-- The Actor is a container for parallel execution\n\n-- Inside an Actor's Script:\nlocal RunService = game:GetService(\"RunService\")\n\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()\n    -- SERIAL phase (safe to access shared state)\n\n    task.desynchronize()  -- switch to PARALLEL\n    -- Now running on a separate thread!\n    -- Can ONLY read shared state, not write\n    -- Do expensive computations here:\n    local result = heavyComputation()\n\n    task.synchronize()    -- back to SERIAL\n    -- Safe to write again\n    applyResult(result)\nend)\n\n-- SharedTable: thread-safe data sharing\nlocal st = SharedTable.new()\nst.value = 42\n-- Can be read from parallel, written from serial"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "Parallel Rules", "text": "In parallel phase: you can READ Instances but NOT write properties, NOT create/destroy instances, and NOT fire events. Violations will error."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚡ Performance Best Practices", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- 1. Cache service lookups\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\"Players\")  -- do once\n-- NOT: game:GetService(\"Players\") every frame\n\n-- 2. Avoid creating tables in hot loops\nlocal reusable = {}  -- create once\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function(dt)\n    table.clear(reusable)  -- reuse\n    -- ... fill reusable ...\nend)\n\n-- 3. Use table.create for pre-allocation\nlocal grid = table.create(10000, 0)  -- avoids resizing\n\n-- 4. Avoid string concatenation in loops\nlocal parts = table.create(100)\nfor i = 1, 100 do parts[i] = tostring(i) end\nlocal result = table.concat(parts, \",\")\n\n-- 5. Debounce expensive operations\nlocal function debounce(fn, interval)\n    local last = 0\n    return function(...)\n        if tick() - last < interval then return end\n        last = tick()\n        return fn(...)\n    end\nend\n\n-- 6. Bulk operations over per-frame\n-- BAD: move 100 parts every frame individually\n-- GOOD: use BulkMoveTo for many parts\nworkspace:BulkMoveTo({part1, part2, ...}, {cf1, cf2, ...})\n\n-- 7. Spatial indexing for proximity checks\n-- Instead of checking distance to every enemy:\nlocal function getNearby(pos, radius)\n    return workspace:GetPartBoundsInRadius(pos, radius, params)\nend\n\n-- 8. Object pooling\nlocal pool = {}\nlocal function acquire()\n    return table.remove(pool) or Instance.new(\"Part\")\nend\nlocal function release(obj)\n    obj.Parent = nil\n    table.insert(pool, obj)\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Profiling", "text": "Use the <strong>MicroProfiler</strong> (Ctrl+F6 in Studio) to find bottlenecks. Check <strong>Script Performance</strong> in the Developer Console for per-script CPU usage. Use <code>debug.profilebegin()/profileend()</code> for custom profiling labels."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📋 Complete Checklist", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>✅ Performance Checklist:</strong><ul><li>Cache GetService and FindFirstChild results</li><li>Use <code>local</code> for all variables (register-based, faster)</li><li>Pre-allocate tables with <code>table.create</code></li><li>Use <code>table.concat</code> instead of repeated <code>..</code></li><li>Debounce expensive callbacks (Touched, Changed)</li><li>Disconnect unused event connections</li><li>Use <code>workspace:BulkMoveTo</code> for many parts</li><li>Use spatial queries instead of distance loops</li><li>Pool frequently created/destroyed objects</li><li>Use Parallel Luau for heavy computation</li><li>Enable Native codegen with <code>--!native</code> comment</li><li>Profile with MicroProfiler before optimizing</li></ul>"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What must you call before writing to Instances in Parallel Luau?", "options": [{"text": "task.desynchronize()", "correct": false}, {"text": "task.synchronize()", "correct": true}, {"text": "task.wait()", "correct": false}, {"text": "Nothing", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! You must call <code>task.synchronize()</code> to return to the serial phase before modifying shared state.", "incorrect": "You must <code>task.synchronize()</code> (return to serial) before writing to Instances."}}, {"id": 24, "title": "Lighting & Atmosphere", "icon": "💡", "color": "#fde68a", "desc": "Lighting service, atmosphere, sky, bloom, color correction, and day/night cycles", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🌅 Lighting Service", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "The <strong>Lighting</strong> service controls global illumination, time of day, shadows, and post-processing effects. It's the single most impactful service for visual quality."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local Lighting = game:GetService(\"Lighting\")\n\n-- Time of day (0-24 hours)\nLighting.ClockTime = 14.5     -- 2:30 PM\nLighting.TimeOfDay = \"14:30:00\"  -- string format\n\n-- Core properties\nLighting.Brightness = 2\nLighting.Ambient = Color3.fromRGB(40, 40, 50)\nLighting.OutdoorAmbient = Color3.fromRGB(70, 70, 80)\nLighting.ColorShift_Top = Color3.fromRGB(255, 240, 220)\nLighting.EnvironmentDiffuseScale = 1\nLighting.EnvironmentSpecularScale = 1\nLighting.GlobalShadows = true\nLighting.ShadowSoftness = 0.2\nLighting.Technology = Enum.Technology.Future\n\n-- Fog\nLighting.FogStart = 0\nLighting.FogEnd = 1000\nLighting.FogColor = Color3.fromRGB(180, 190, 210)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Technology", "text": "<code>Enum.Technology.Future</code> enables the most realistic lighting with real-time global illumination. Use <code>ShadowMap</code> for a good balance."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🌫️ Atmosphere & Sky", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Atmosphere: realistic scattering\nlocal atm = Instance.new(\"Atmosphere\")\natm.Density = 0.3\natm.Offset = 0.25\natm.Color = Color3.fromRGB(200, 170, 130)\natm.Decay = Color3.fromRGB(100, 60, 40)\natm.Glare = 0\natm.Haze = 0\natm.Parent = Lighting\n\n-- Sky: custom skybox\nlocal sky = Instance.new(\"Sky\")\nsky.SkyboxBk = \"rbxassetid://YOUR_ID\"\nsky.SkyboxDn = \"rbxassetid://YOUR_ID\"\nsky.SkyboxFt = \"rbxassetid://YOUR_ID\"\nsky.SkyboxLf = \"rbxassetid://YOUR_ID\"\nsky.SkyboxRt = \"rbxassetid://YOUR_ID\"\nsky.SkyboxUp = \"rbxassetid://YOUR_ID\"\nsky.StarCount = 3000\nsky.CelestialBodiesShown = true\nsky.Parent = Lighting"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "✨ Post-Processing Effects", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Bloom: glow on bright areas\nlocal bloom = Instance.new(\"BloomEffect\")\nbloom.Intensity = 0.5\nbloom.Size = 24\nbloom.Threshold = 0.8\nbloom.Parent = Lighting\n\n-- Color Correction\nlocal cc = Instance.new(\"ColorCorrectionEffect\")\ncc.Brightness = 0.05\ncc.Contrast = 0.1\ncc.Saturation = 0.15\ncc.TintColor = Color3.fromRGB(255, 250, 240)\ncc.Parent = Lighting\n\n-- Depth of Field\nlocal dof = Instance.new(\"DepthOfFieldEffect\")\ndof.FarIntensity = 0.3\ndof.FocusDistance = 20\ndof.InFocusRadius = 30\ndof.NearIntensity = 0\ndof.Parent = Lighting\n\n-- Sun Rays\nlocal rays = Instance.new(\"SunRaysEffect\")\nrays.Intensity = 0.1\nrays.Spread = 0.5\nrays.Parent = Lighting"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "Performance", "text": "Post-processing runs on the GPU. On mobile, consider disabling <code>DepthOfFieldEffect</code> and reducing <code>BloomEffect.Size</code>."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🌙 Day/Night Cycle", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Server script: smooth day/night cycle\nlocal Lighting = game:GetService(\"Lighting\")\nlocal RunService = game:GetService(\"RunService\")\n\nlocal MINUTES_PER_DAY = 12  -- real minutes per game day\n\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function(dt)\n    local minutesPerSec = (24 * 60) / (MINUTES_PER_DAY * 60)\n    local increment = minutesPerSec * dt / 60\n    Lighting.ClockTime = (Lighting.ClockTime + increment) % 24\nend)\n\n-- Adjust ambient based on time\nlocal function updateLighting()\n    local t = Lighting.ClockTime\n    local isNight = t < 6 or t > 19\n    if isNight then\n        Lighting.Ambient = Color3.fromRGB(20, 20, 35)\n        Lighting.Brightness = 0.5\n    else\n        Lighting.Ambient = Color3.fromRGB(50, 50, 60)\n        Lighting.Brightness = 2\n    end\nend\n\nLighting:GetPropertyChangedSignal(\"ClockTime\"):Connect(updateLighting)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "Which <code>Lighting.Technology</code> gives the most realistic results?", "options": [{"text": "Compatibility", "correct": false}, {"text": "Voxel", "correct": false}, {"text": "ShadowMap", "correct": false}, {"text": "Future", "correct": true}], "correct": "Correct! <code>Future</code> enables real-time global illumination.", "incorrect": "<code>Future</code> technology provides the most realistic lighting."}}, {"id": 25, "title": "Sound & Music", "icon": "🔊", "color": "#38bdf8", "desc": "SoundService, Sound objects, groups, 3D audio, and music systems", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🔈 Sound Basics", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Playing a sound\nlocal sound = Instance.new(\"Sound\")\nsound.SoundId = \"rbxassetid://123456789\"\nsound.Volume = 0.5\nsound.PlaybackSpeed = 1\nsound.Looped = false\nsound.Parent = workspace    -- 2D (global) sound\n\nsound:Play()\nsound.Ended:Wait()\nsound:Destroy()\n\n-- 3D positional audio (attach to a Part)\nlocal sfx = Instance.new(\"Sound\")\nsfx.SoundId = \"rbxassetid://123456789\"\nsfx.RollOffMode = Enum.RollOffMode.InverseTapered\nsfx.RollOffMinDistance = 10\nsfx.RollOffMaxDistance = 100\nsfx.Parent = workspace.SomePart  -- position matters!\nsfx:Play()\n\n-- Preloading for instant playback\nlocal ContentProvider = game:GetService(\"ContentProvider\")\nContentProvider:PreloadAsync({sound})"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "2D vs 3D", "text": "Sound parented to <strong>Workspace/SoundService</strong> = 2D (everywhere). Sound parented to a <strong>BasePart</strong> = 3D (positional)."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏛️ SoundService & Groups", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local SoundService = game:GetService(\"SoundService\")\n\nSoundService.AmbientReverb = Enum.ReverbType.ConcertHall\nSoundService.DistanceFactor = 3.33\nSoundService.DopplerScale = 1\n\n-- SoundGroups: control volume of categories\nlocal musicGroup = Instance.new(\"SoundGroup\")\nmusicGroup.Name = \"Music\"\nmusicGroup.Volume = 0.8\nmusicGroup.Parent = SoundService\n\nlocal sfxGroup = Instance.new(\"SoundGroup\")\nsfxGroup.Name = \"SFX\"\nsfxGroup.Volume = 1\nsfxGroup.Parent = SoundService\n\n-- Assign sounds to groups\nsound.SoundGroup = musicGroup\n\n-- Sound Effects (children of Sound)\nlocal reverb = Instance.new(\"ReverbSoundEffect\")\nreverb.DecayTime = 1.5\nreverb.Density = 1\nreverb.Parent = sound\n\nlocal eq = Instance.new(\"EqualizerSoundEffect\")\neq.LowGain = 0\neq.MidGain = -2\neq.HighGain = 3\neq.Parent = sound"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎵 Music System", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Music manager with crossfade\nlocal TweenService = game:GetService(\"TweenService\")\nlocal currentTrack = nil\n\nlocal function playMusic(id, fadeTime)\n    fadeTime = fadeTime or 1\n    -- Fade out old\n    if currentTrack then\n        local old = currentTrack\n        TweenService:Create(old, TweenInfo.new(fadeTime), {\n            Volume = 0\n        }):Play()\n        task.delay(fadeTime, function() old:Destroy() end)\n    end\n    -- Fade in new\n    local s = Instance.new(\"Sound\")\n    s.SoundId = id\n    s.Looped = true\n    s.Volume = 0\n    s.Parent = workspace\n    s:Play()\n    TweenService:Create(s, TweenInfo.new(fadeTime), {\n        Volume = 0.7\n    }):Play()\n    currentTrack = s\nend\n\nlocal function stopMusic(fadeTime)\n    if not currentTrack then return end\n    local old = currentTrack\n    currentTrack = nil\n    TweenService:Create(old, TweenInfo.new(fadeTime or 1), {\n        Volume = 0\n    }):Play()\n    task.delay(fadeTime or 1, function() old:Destroy() end)\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Audio Limits", "text": "Roblox supports up to <strong>256 simultaneous sounds</strong>. Always <code>:Destroy()</code> finished one-shot sounds."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "How do you make a Sound 3D positional?", "options": [{"text": "Set RollOffMode property", "correct": false}, {"text": "Parent it to a BasePart", "correct": true}, {"text": "Set Volume to 3D", "correct": false}, {"text": "Use SoundService:SetListener()", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Parenting a Sound to a BasePart makes it positional in 3D space.", "incorrect": "Parent sounds to a <strong>BasePart</strong> for 3D audio."}}, {"id": 26, "title": "PathfindingService & NPC AI", "icon": "🤖", "color": "#4ade80", "desc": "Navigation, pathfinding, waypoints, and NPC behavior patterns", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🗺️ PathfindingService Basics", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local PathfindingService = game:GetService(\"PathfindingService\")\n\nlocal path = PathfindingService:CreatePath({\n    AgentRadius = 2,\n    AgentHeight = 5,\n    AgentCanJump = true,\n    AgentCanClimb = false,\n    WaypointSpacing = 4,\n    Costs = {\n        Water = 20,\n        Mud = 10,\n        DangerZone = math.huge\n    }\n})\n\nlocal start = npc.HumanoidRootPart.Position\nlocal goal = Vector3.new(50, 0, 50)\n\npath:ComputeAsync(start, goal)\n\nif path.Status == Enum.PathStatus.Success then\n    local waypoints = path:GetWaypoints()\n    for _, wp in waypoints do\n        print(wp.Position, wp.Action)\n    end\nelse\n    warn(\"Path failed:\", path.Status)\nend"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Property", "Description"], "rows": [["AgentRadius", "Half-width of character (studs)"], ["AgentHeight", "Height of character (studs)"], ["AgentCanJump", "Allow jump navigation links"], ["AgentCanClimb", "Allow ladder/truss climbing"], ["WaypointSpacing", "Distance between waypoints"], ["Costs", "Table of PathfindingModifier costs"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🚶 NPC Movement", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local function moveNPC(npc, goal)\n    local humanoid = npc:FindFirstChildOfClass(\"Humanoid\")\n    local rootPart = npc:FindFirstChild(\"HumanoidRootPart\")\n    if not humanoid or not rootPart then return end\n\n    local path = PathfindingService:CreatePath({\n        AgentRadius = 2, AgentHeight = 5, AgentCanJump = true,\n    })\n    path:ComputeAsync(rootPart.Position, goal)\n    if path.Status ~= Enum.PathStatus.Success then return end\n\n    local waypoints = path:GetWaypoints()\n\n    local blocked\n    blocked = path.Blocked:Connect(function(blockedIdx)\n        blocked:Disconnect()\n        moveNPC(npc, goal)  -- recompute\n    end)\n\n    for i, wp in waypoints do\n        if wp.Action == Enum.PathWaypointAction.Jump then\n            humanoid.Jump = true\n        end\n        humanoid:MoveTo(wp.Position)\n        local reached = humanoid.MoveToFinished:Wait()\n        if not reached then\n            blocked:Disconnect()\n            moveNPC(npc, goal)\n            return\n        end\n    end\n    blocked:Disconnect()\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "PathfindingModifiers", "text": "Add <code>PathfindingModifier</code> instances to parts to mark them with custom costs, or set <code>PassThrough = true</code> for doors."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🧠 AI State Machine", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local States = { IDLE = 1, PATROL = 2, CHASE = 3, ATTACK = 4 }\n\nlocal function updateAI(npc, state, target)\n    local root = npc:FindFirstChild(\"HumanoidRootPart\")\n    if not root then return state end\n\n    local nearest, dist = findNearestPlayer(root.Position)\n\n    -- Transitions\n    if state == States.IDLE or state == States.PATROL then\n        if nearest and dist < 40 then\n            return States.CHASE\n        end\n    elseif state == States.CHASE then\n        if not nearest or dist > 60 then\n            return States.PATROL\n        elseif dist < 5 then\n            return States.ATTACK\n        else\n            moveNPC(npc, nearest.Character.HumanoidRootPart.Position)\n        end\n    elseif state == States.ATTACK then\n        if not nearest or dist > 10 then\n            return States.CHASE\n        end\n        -- deal damage...\n    end\n    return state\nend\n\nlocal function findNearestPlayer(pos)\n    local best, bestDist = nil, math.huge\n    for _, p in game.Players:GetPlayers() do\n        local c = p.Character\n        if c and c:FindFirstChild(\"HumanoidRootPart\") then\n            local d = (c.HumanoidRootPart.Position - pos).Magnitude\n            if d < bestDist then best, bestDist = p, d end\n        end\n    end\n    return best, bestDist\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Performance", "text": "For many NPCs, stagger <code>:ComputeAsync()</code> calls across frames using <code>task.defer()</code>. PathfindingService has internal rate limits."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>path.Blocked</code> fire when?", "options": [{"text": "When the NPC stops moving", "correct": false}, {"text": "When an obstacle blocks a future waypoint", "correct": true}, {"text": "When the path can't be computed", "correct": false}, {"text": "When the NPC reaches the goal", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>path.Blocked</code> fires when something obstructs a waypoint ahead.", "incorrect": "<code>path.Blocked</code> fires when a waypoint ahead becomes blocked — recompute the path."}}, {"id": 27, "title": "MarketplaceService & Monetization", "icon": "💰", "color": "#fb923c", "desc": "Developer products, game passes, subscriptions, and purchase prompts", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🎫 Game Passes", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Game Passes</strong> are one-time purchases that grant permanent perks. Players buy them once and own them forever."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local MPS = game:GetService(\"MarketplaceService\")\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\"Players\")\n\nlocal VIP_PASS_ID = 123456789\n\nlocal function hasPass(player, passId)\n    local ok, owns = pcall(MPS.UserOwnsGamePassAsync, MPS, player.UserId, passId)\n    return ok and owns\nend\n\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\n    if hasPass(player, VIP_PASS_ID) then\n        player:SetAttribute(\"VIP\", true)\n    end\n\n    player.CharacterAdded:Connect(function(char)\n        if player:GetAttribute(\"VIP\") then\n            local h = char:WaitForChild(\"Humanoid\")\n            h.WalkSpeed = 24  -- VIP speed boost\n        end\n    end)\nend)\n\n-- Detect purchase mid-game (SERVER)\nMPS.PromptGamePassPurchaseFinished:Connect(function(player, passId, purchased)\n    if purchased and passId == VIP_PASS_ID then\n        player:SetAttribute(\"VIP\", true)\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Prompt purchase (CLIENT)\nMPS:PromptGamePassPurchase(player, VIP_PASS_ID)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "Server-Side Validation", "text": "Never trust the client for ownership. Always use <code>UserOwnsGamePassAsync</code> on the <strong>server</strong>. Wrap in <code>pcall</code>."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "💎 Developer Products", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Developer Products</strong> are repeatable purchases — coins, gems, respawns. Players can buy them multiple times."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local PRODUCTS = {\n    [111111] = { name = \"100 Coins\",  coins = 100 },\n    [222222] = { name = \"500 Coins\",  coins = 500 },\n    [333333] = { name = \"Extra Life\", lives = 1 },\n}\n\n-- CRITICAL: ProcessReceipt callback (SERVER)\nMPS.ProcessReceipt = function(receiptInfo)\n    local player = game.Players:GetPlayerByUserId(receiptInfo.PlayerId)\n    if not player then\n        return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.NotProcessedYet\n    end\n\n    local product = PRODUCTS[receiptInfo.ProductId]\n    if not product then\n        return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.NotProcessedYet\n    end\n\n    local ok = pcall(function()\n        if product.coins then\n            local data = playerData[player.UserId]\n            data.coins += product.coins\n        end\n        if product.lives then\n            local data = playerData[player.UserId]\n            data.lives += product.lives\n        end\n    end)\n\n    if ok then\n        -- Save immediately!\n        pcall(function()\n            dataStore:SetAsync(\"user_\" .. player.UserId, playerData[player.UserId])\n        end)\n        return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.PurchaseGranted\n    end\n    return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.NotProcessedYet\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "danger", "title": "ProcessReceipt is Critical", "text": "If <code>ProcessReceipt</code> doesn't return <code>PurchaseGranted</code>, Roblox will <strong>retry</strong> later. Save data <strong>before</strong> returning."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏪 Product Info & Subscriptions", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Get product info for display\nlocal info = MPS:GetProductInfo(123456789, Enum.InfoType.GamePass)\nprint(info.Name)         -- \"VIP Pass\"\nprint(info.PriceInRobux) -- 499\n\n-- Subscriptions (recurring payments)\nlocal SUB_ID = \"your-subscription-id\"\n\nlocal ok, sub = pcall(function()\n    return MPS:GetUserSubscriptionStatusAsync(player, SUB_ID)\nend)\nif ok and sub.IsSubscribed then\n    print(\"Active subscription!\")\nend\n\nMPS:PromptSubscriptionPurchase(player, SUB_ID)"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Type", "Repeatable", "Use Case"], "rows": [["Game Pass", "No (one-time)", "VIP, 2x XP, special abilities"], ["Developer Product", "Yes (many times)", "Currency, consumables, respawns"], ["Subscription", "Recurring monthly", "Premium tiers, exclusive access"], ["Badge", "Free (achievement)", "Milestones, rewards, bragging"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🛡️ Anti-Exploit: Receipt Logging", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local receiptStore = DSS:GetDataStore(\"PurchaseReceipts\")\n\nMPS.ProcessReceipt = function(info)\n    local key = info.PlayerId .. \"_\" .. info.PurchaseId\n\n    -- Idempotency: check if already processed\n    local ok, existing = pcall(receiptStore.GetAsync, receiptStore, key)\n    if ok and existing then\n        return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.PurchaseGranted\n    end\n\n    -- Grant product...\n    local granted = grantProduct(info)\n    if not granted then\n        return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.NotProcessedYet\n    end\n\n    -- Log receipt\n    pcall(receiptStore.SetAsync, receiptStore, key, {\n        productId = info.ProductId,\n        time = os.time(),\n        amount = info.CurrencySpent,\n    })\n    return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.PurchaseGranted\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Testing", "text": "In Studio, purchases are <strong>free</strong> test currency. Toggle <strong>API Services</strong> in Game Settings to enable MarketplaceService."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What happens if <code>ProcessReceipt</code> returns <code>NotProcessedYet</code>?", "options": [{"text": "The purchase is cancelled", "correct": false}, {"text": "Roblox retries the callback later", "correct": true}, {"text": "The player is refunded immediately", "correct": false}, {"text": "An error is thrown", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Roblox <strong>retries</strong> ProcessReceipt until <code>PurchaseGranted</code> is returned.", "incorrect": "Roblox retries until <code>PurchaseGranted</code> — ensuring players get what they paid for."}}, {"id": 28, "title": "DataStoreService Deep Dive", "icon": "🗄️", "color": "#00ffb3", "desc": "OrderedDataStores, versioning, session locking, budgets, and migration", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🏆 OrderedDataStores", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>OrderedDataStore</strong> only stores integers but enables <strong>sorted queries</strong> — perfect for leaderboards, rankings, and top-N lists."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local DSS = game:GetService(\"DataStoreService\")\nlocal leaderboard = DSS:GetOrderedDataStore(\"Wins_v1\")\n\n-- Set a player's score\nlocal function setScore(userId: number, score: number)\n    pcall(leaderboard.SetAsync, leaderboard, tostring(userId), score)\nend\n\n-- Get top 50 players (descending)\nlocal function getTopPlayers(count: number)\n    local ok, pages = pcall(function()\n        return leaderboard:GetSortedAsync(\n            false,   -- ascending = false (highest first)\n            count    -- page size\n        )\n    end)\n    if not ok then return {} end\n\n    local result = {}\n    local page = pages:GetCurrentPage()\n    for rank, entry in ipairs(page) do\n        table.insert(result, {\n            rank = rank,\n            userId = tonumber(entry.key),\n            score = entry.value,\n        })\n    end\n    return result\nend\n\n-- Paginate through all results\nlocal function getAllSorted()\n    local pages = leaderboard:GetSortedAsync(false, 100)\n    local all = {}\n    while true do\n        for _, entry in pages:GetCurrentPage() do\n            table.insert(all, entry)\n        end\n        if pages.IsFinished then break end\n        pages:AdvanceToNextPageAsync()\n    end\n    return all\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔄 Versioning & Rollback", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local store = DSS:GetDataStore(\"PlayerData_v2\")\n\n-- List past versions of a key\nlocal function listVersions(key: string)\n    local ok, pages = pcall(function()\n        return store:ListVersionsAsync(key, Enum.SortDirection.Descending, 10)\n    end)\n    if not ok then return {} end\n\n    local versions = {}\n    for _, info in pages:GetCurrentPage() do\n        table.insert(versions, {\n            version = info.Version,\n            createdTime = info.CreatedTime,\n            isDeleted = info.IsDeleted,\n        })\n    end\n    return versions\nend\n\n-- Restore a previous version\nlocal function rollback(key: string, version: string)\n    local ok, data = pcall(function()\n        return store:GetVersionAsync(key, version)\n    end)\n    if ok and data then\n        pcall(store.SetAsync, store, key, data)\n        return true\n    end\n    return false\nend\n\n-- Remove a key (soft delete, versioned)\nlocal function softDelete(key: string)\n    pcall(store.RemoveAsync, store, key)\n    -- Previous versions still accessible via ListVersionsAsync\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Version Retention", "text": "Roblox keeps versions for <strong>30 days</strong>. After that, old versions are purged. Plan backups accordingly."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔒 Session Locking Pattern", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Session locking</strong> prevents two servers from modifying the same player's data simultaneously, which causes data loss."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local HttpService = game:GetService(\"HttpService\")\nlocal SERVER_ID = HttpService:GenerateGUID(false)\nlocal LOCK_TIMEOUT = 300 -- 5 minutes\n\nlocal function acquireLock(store, key)\n    local acquired = false\n    pcall(function()\n        store:UpdateAsync(key .. \"_lock\", function(old)\n            local now = os.time()\n            if old == nil or now - (old.time or 0) > LOCK_TIMEOUT then\n                acquired = true\n                return { owner = SERVER_ID, time = now }\n            end\n            if old.owner == SERVER_ID then\n                acquired = true\n                old.time = now\n                return old\n            end\n            return nil -- abort, someone else owns it\n        end)\n    end)\n    return acquired\nend\n\nlocal function releaseLock(store, key)\n    pcall(function()\n        store:UpdateAsync(key .. \"_lock\", function(old)\n            if old and old.owner == SERVER_ID then\n                return nil -- remove lock\n            end\n            return nil\n        end)\n    end)\nend\n\n-- Usage in PlayerAdded\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\n    local key = \"user_\" .. player.UserId\n    if acquireLock(store, key) then\n        local data = loadData(player)\n        playerData[player.UserId] = data\n    else\n        warn(\"Data locked by another server!\")\n        -- Retry or kick player\n    end\nend)\n\ngame:BindToClose(function()\n    for _, player in Players:GetPlayers() do\n        local key = \"user_\" .. player.UserId\n        saveData(player, playerData[player.UserId])\n        releaseLock(store, key)\n    end\nend)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📊 Budget Management", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Check remaining budget before requests\nlocal function hasBudget(requestType: Enum.DataStoreRequestType): boolean\n    local budget = DSS:GetRequestBudgetForRequestType(requestType)\n    return budget > 0\nend\n\n-- Request queue system\nlocal requestQueue = {}\nlocal processing = false\n\nlocal function enqueue(fn)\n    table.insert(requestQueue, fn)\n    if not processing then\n        processing = true\n        task.spawn(function()\n            while #requestQueue > 0 do\n                local req = table.remove(requestQueue, 1)\n                if hasBudget(Enum.DataStoreRequestType.SetIncrementAsync) then\n                    pcall(req)\n                else\n                    task.wait(1) -- wait for budget\n                    table.insert(requestQueue, 1, req) -- re-add\n                end\n                task.wait(0.1)\n            end\n            processing = false\n        end)\n    end\nend\n\n-- Auto-save system with budget awareness\nlocal AUTO_SAVE_INTERVAL = 300 -- 5 min\ntask.spawn(function()\n    while true do\n        task.wait(AUTO_SAVE_INTERVAL)\n        for _, player in Players:GetPlayers() do\n            enqueue(function()\n                saveData(player, playerData[player.UserId])\n            end)\n        end\n    end\nend)"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Request Type", "Budget Formula"], "rows": [["GetAsync", "60 + numPlayers * 10"], ["SetAsync / UpdateAsync", "60 + numPlayers * 10"], ["GetSortedAsync", "5 + numPlayers * 2"], ["SetIncrementSortedAsync", "5 + numPlayers * 2"], ["OnUpdate", "30 + numPlayers * 5"]]}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What is the main advantage of <code>OrderedDataStore</code> over regular DataStore?", "options": [{"text": "It stores more data", "correct": false}, {"text": "It enables sorted queries for leaderboards", "correct": true}, {"text": "It has no rate limits", "correct": false}, {"text": "It works on the client", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! OrderedDataStore stores integers and enables <code>GetSortedAsync</code> for leaderboards.", "incorrect": "OrderedDataStore's key feature is <strong>sorted queries</strong> via <code>GetSortedAsync</code>."}}, {"id": 29, "title": "RemoteEvents & Functions Deep Dive", "icon": "📡", "color": "#c77dff", "desc": "UnreliableRemoteEvents, middleware, batching, type-safe wrappers, and optimization", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "⚡ UnreliableRemoteEvent", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>UnreliableRemoteEvents</strong> use UDP instead of TCP — faster but packets can be <strong>dropped or reordered</strong>. Perfect for high-frequency, non-critical data like position updates."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Create UnreliableRemoteEvent in ReplicatedStorage\n\n-- SERVER: broadcast positions 30x/sec\nlocal unreliable = RS:WaitForChild(\"PositionSync\")\n\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()\n    for _, player in Players:GetPlayers() do\n        local char = player.Character\n        if char and char:FindFirstChild(\"HumanoidRootPart\") then\n            unreliable:FireAllClients(\n                player.UserId,\n                char.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame\n            )\n        end\n    end\nend)\n\n-- CLIENT: interpolate received positions\nlocal positions = {} -- userId -> {target, current}\n\nunreliable.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(userId, cframe)\n    if userId == localPlayer.UserId then return end\n    positions[userId] = positions[userId] or {}\n    positions[userId].target = cframe\nend)\n\n-- Smooth interpolation\nRunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function(dt)\n    for userId, data in positions do\n        if data.target and data.current then\n            data.current = data.current:Lerp(data.target, 10 * dt)\n        else\n            data.current = data.target\n        end\n    end\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "When to Use", "text": "<strong>Use Unreliable for:</strong> positions, rotations, particle effects, cosmetic updates<br><strong>Use Reliable for:</strong> damage, purchases, chat, game state changes"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🛡️ Remote Middleware Pattern", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Type-safe remote wrapper module\n-- ModuleScript in ReplicatedStorage\n\nlocal RemoteManager = {}\nlocal remotes = {}\n\ntype RemoteConfig = {\n    name: string,\n    validate: ((player: Player, ...any) -> boolean)?,\n    rateLimit: number?, -- min seconds between calls\n}\n\nlocal lastCall: {[Player]: {[string]: number}} = {}\n\nfunction RemoteManager.register(config: RemoteConfig)\n    local remote = Instance.new(\"RemoteEvent\")\n    remote.Name = config.name\n    remote.Parent = game.ReplicatedStorage:FindFirstChild(\"Remotes\")\n\n    remotes[config.name] = {\n        remote = remote,\n        config = config,\n    }\n\n    -- Server handler with middleware\n    remote.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, ...)\n        -- Rate limit check\n        if config.rateLimit then\n            lastCall[player] = lastCall[player] or {}\n            local now = tick()\n            local last = lastCall[player][config.name] or 0\n            if now - last < config.rateLimit then return end\n            lastCall[player][config.name] = now\n        end\n\n        -- Validation check\n        if config.validate and not config.validate(player, ...) then\n            warn(\"Invalid remote call:\", config.name, player.Name)\n            return\n        end\n\n        -- Process (override per-remote)\n        if config.onServer then\n            config.onServer(player, ...)\n        end\n    end)\n\n    return remote\nend\n\n-- Usage:\nRemoteManager.register({\n    name = \"DealDamage\",\n    rateLimit = 0.1,\n    validate = function(player, targetId, amount)\n        return type(targetId) == \"number\"\n           and type(amount) == \"number\"\n           and amount > 0 and amount <= 100\n    end,\n    onServer = function(player, targetId, amount)\n        -- safe to process\n    end,\n})"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📦 Remote Batching", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Sending many small remotes is expensive. <strong>Batch</strong> them into a single fire per frame to reduce network overhead."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- CLIENT: batch outgoing events\nlocal batchQueue = {}\nlocal batchRemote = RS:WaitForChild(\"BatchRemote\")\n\nlocal function queueRemote(action: string, data: any)\n    table.insert(batchQueue, {action = action, data = data})\nend\n\n-- Flush once per frame\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()\n    if #batchQueue > 0 then\n        batchRemote:FireServer(batchQueue)\n        table.clear(batchQueue)\n    end\nend)\n\n-- SERVER: process batch\nbatchRemote.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, batch)\n    if type(batch) ~= \"table\" then return end\n    if #batch > 20 then return end -- anti-spam\n\n    for _, item in batch do\n        if type(item) ~= \"table\" then continue end\n        if type(item.action) ~= \"string\" then continue end\n\n        local handler = handlers[item.action]\n        if handler then\n            handler(player, item.data)\n        end\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Register handlers\nlocal handlers = {\n    [\"move\"] = function(player, data)\n        -- handle move\n    end,\n    [\"interact\"] = function(player, data)\n        -- handle interact\n    end,\n}"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📝 Type-Safe Remote Wrappers", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Shared types module (ReplicatedStorage)\nexport type DamagePayload = {\n    targetId: number,\n    amount: number,\n    damageType: \"melee\" | \"ranged\" | \"magic\",\n}\n\nexport type ChatPayload = {\n    message: string,\n    channel: string,\n}\n\n-- Type-safe fire helper (CLIENT)\nlocal function fireDamage(payload: DamagePayload)\n    assert(typeof(payload.targetId) == \"number\")\n    assert(payload.amount > 0 and payload.amount <= 100)\n    remotes.DealDamage:FireServer(payload)\nend\n\n-- Type-safe handler (SERVER)\nlocal function onDamage(player: Player, payload: DamagePayload)\n    if typeof(payload) ~= \"table\" then return end\n    local target = findEntityById(payload.targetId)\n    if not target then return end\n\n    -- Distance check (anti-exploit)\n    local dist = (player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.Position\n        - target.Position).Magnitude\n    if dist > 15 then return end\n\n    applyDamage(target, payload.amount, payload.damageType)\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Network Data Limits", "text": "Single remote fire: <strong>1KB soft limit</strong> (warn), <strong>256KB hard limit</strong> (drop). Keep payloads small!"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "When should you use <code>UnreliableRemoteEvent</code> over <code>RemoteEvent</code>?", "options": [{"text": "For purchase transactions", "correct": false}, {"text": "For high-frequency position updates", "correct": true}, {"text": "For chat messages", "correct": false}, {"text": "For DataStore saves", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! UnreliableRemoteEvents use UDP — ideal for frequent, non-critical data like positions.", "incorrect": "UnreliableRemoteEvents are for <strong>high-frequency, loss-tolerant</strong> data like positions."}}, {"id": 30, "title": "TweenService Deep Dive", "icon": "🎥", "color": "#ffd93d", "desc": "Model tweening, chained sequences, UI animations, custom easing, and spring physics", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🎭 Tweening Models", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "You can't tween a Model directly. Tween its <strong>PrimaryPart's CFrame</strong> and all welded parts follow along."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local TweenService = game:GetService(\"TweenService\")\n\n-- Tween a model by its PrimaryPart\nlocal function tweenModel(model: Model, goal: CFrame, duration: number)\n    local primary = model.PrimaryPart\n    if not primary then warn(\"No PrimaryPart!\") return end\n\n    -- Weld all parts to PrimaryPart first\n    for _, part in model:GetDescendants() do\n        if part:IsA(\"BasePart\") and part ~= primary then\n            local weld = Instance.new(\"WeldConstraint\")\n            weld.Part0 = primary\n            weld.Part1 = part\n            weld.Parent = part\n            part.Anchored = false\n        end\n    end\n    primary.Anchored = true\n\n    local tween = TweenService:Create(primary, TweenInfo.new(\n        duration, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.InOut\n    ), { CFrame = goal })\n\n    tween:Play()\n    return tween\nend\n\n-- Sliding door example\nlocal door = workspace.SlidingDoor\nlocal openPos = door.PrimaryPart.CFrame * CFrame.new(0, 5, 0)\nlocal closedPos = door.PrimaryPart.CFrame\n\nlocal isOpen = false\nlocal function toggleDoor()\n    isOpen = not isOpen\n    tweenModel(door, if isOpen then openPos else closedPos, 0.8)\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔗 Chained & Parallel Sequences", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Sequential tween chain\nlocal function tweenSequence(part, steps: {{properties: {}, time: number}})\n    for _, step in steps do\n        local tween = TweenService:Create(\n            part,\n            TweenInfo.new(step.time, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad),\n            step.properties\n        )\n        tween:Play()\n        tween.Completed:Wait()\n    end\nend\n\n-- Usage: bounce effect\ntweenSequence(part, {\n    {properties = {Position = Vector3.new(0, 20, 0)}, time = 0.5},\n    {properties = {Position = Vector3.new(0, 5, 0)},  time = 0.3},\n    {properties = {Position = Vector3.new(0, 12, 0)}, time = 0.2},\n    {properties = {Position = Vector3.new(0, 5, 0)},  time = 0.15},\n})\n\n-- Parallel tweens (play multiple at once)\nlocal function tweenParallel(tweens: {Tween})\n    for _, tween in tweens do tween:Play() end\n    -- Wait for longest\n    for _, tween in tweens do tween.Completed:Wait() end\nend\n\n-- Fade + scale simultaneously\ntweenParallel({\n    TweenService:Create(frame, TweenInfo.new(0.3), {\n        BackgroundTransparency = 0\n    }),\n    TweenService:Create(frame, TweenInfo.new(0.4, Enum.EasingStyle.Back), {\n        Size = UDim2.fromScale(0.5, 0.5)\n    }),\n})"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📱 UI Animation Patterns", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Notification slide-in\nlocal function showNotification(text: string)\n    local frame = notifTemplate:Clone()\n    frame.Text.Text = text\n    frame.Position = UDim2.new(1, 20, 0, 0) -- off-screen right\n    frame.Parent = screenGui\n\n    -- Slide in\n    TweenService:Create(frame, TweenInfo.new(0.4, Enum.EasingStyle.Back), {\n        Position = UDim2.new(1, -320, 0, 0)\n    }):Play()\n\n    task.wait(3)\n\n    -- Slide out + fade\n    local out = TweenService:Create(frame, TweenInfo.new(0.3), {\n        Position = UDim2.new(1, 20, 0, 0),\n        BackgroundTransparency = 1,\n    })\n    out:Play()\n    out.Completed:Wait()\n    frame:Destroy()\nend\n\n-- Button hover effect\nlocal function addHoverEffect(button: TextButton)\n    local originalSize = button.Size\n    local hoverSize = UDim2.new(\n        originalSize.X.Scale * 1.05, originalSize.X.Offset,\n        originalSize.Y.Scale * 1.05, originalSize.Y.Offset\n    )\n    button.MouseEnter:Connect(function()\n        TweenService:Create(button, TweenInfo.new(0.15), {\n            Size = hoverSize\n        }):Play()\n    end)\n    button.MouseLeave:Connect(function()\n        TweenService:Create(button, TweenInfo.new(0.15), {\n            Size = originalSize\n        }):Play()\n    end)\nend\n\n-- Pulsing health bar\nlocal function pulseHealthBar(bar, low)\n    if low then\n        TweenService:Create(bar, TweenInfo.new(0.5,\n            Enum.EasingStyle.Sine, Enum.EasingDirection.InOut,\n            -1, true -- infinite, reversing\n        ), { BackgroundColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(255, 50, 50) }):Play()\n    end\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🌀 Spring Physics Simulation", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Simple spring for smooth following\nlocal Spring = {}\nSpring.__index = Spring\n\nfunction Spring.new(stiffness: number, damping: number)\n    return setmetatable({\n        target = 0,\n        position = 0,\n        velocity = 0,\n        stiffness = stiffness or 200,\n        damping = damping or 20,\n    }, Spring)\nend\n\nfunction Spring:update(dt: number): number\n    local force = self.stiffness * (self.target - self.position)\n    local dampForce = self.damping * self.velocity\n    local acceleration = force - dampForce\n\n    self.velocity += acceleration * dt\n    self.position += self.velocity * dt\n    return self.position\nend\n\n-- Usage: smooth camera offset\nlocal camSpringX = Spring.new(180, 18)\nlocal camSpringY = Spring.new(180, 18)\n\nRunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function(dt)\n    camSpringX.target = mouse.X\n    camSpringY.target = mouse.Y\n    local sx = camSpringX:update(dt)\n    local sy = camSpringY:update(dt)\n    camera.CFrame = baseCFrame * CFrame.new(sx * 0.001, sy * 0.001, 0)\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "When to Use Springs vs Tweens", "text": "<strong>Tweens:</strong> predefined start/end, fixed duration<br><strong>Springs:</strong> dynamic targets, responsive to input, physically plausible motion"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "How do you tween a Model's position?", "options": [{"text": "Tween the Model.Position directly", "correct": false}, {"text": "Tween PrimaryPart.CFrame with welded parts", "correct": true}, {"text": "Use Model:MoveTo() in a loop", "correct": false}, {"text": "Tween each part individually", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Tween the PrimaryPart's CFrame — welded parts follow automatically.", "incorrect": "Tween the <strong>PrimaryPart.CFrame</strong> and weld all other parts to it."}}, {"id": 31, "title": "UserInputService Deep Dive", "icon": "🕹️", "color": "#ff79c6", "desc": "ContextActionService, gamepad support, mobile input, drag-and-drop, and key combos", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🎮 ContextActionService", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>ContextActionService</strong> is superior to UIS for gameplay input. Actions can be <strong>bound/unbound dynamically</strong>, support <strong>mobile buttons</strong> auto-creation, and handle <strong>priority stacking</strong>."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local CAS = game:GetService(\"ContextActionService\")\n\n-- Bind an action (works on keyboard + gamepad + mobile)\nCAS:BindAction(\n    \"Sprint\",                          -- action name\n    function(actionName, state, input)\n        if state == Enum.UserInputState.Begin then\n            humanoid.WalkSpeed = 32\n        elseif state == Enum.UserInputState.End then\n            humanoid.WalkSpeed = 16\n        end\n    end,\n    true,                              -- create mobile button\n    Enum.KeyCode.LeftShift,            -- keyboard\n    Enum.KeyCode.ButtonL2              -- gamepad\n)\n\n-- Customize mobile button\nCAS:SetTitle(\"Sprint\", \"RUN\")\nCAS:SetPosition(\"Sprint\", UDim2.new(1, -70, 1, -120))\nCAS:SetImage(\"Sprint\", \"rbxassetid://123456\")\n\n-- Priority: higher priority overrides lower\n-- E.g., \"VehicleBrake\" overrides \"Sprint\" on the same key\nCAS:BindActionAtPriority(\"VehicleBrake\", brakeFunc, true,\n    Enum.ContextActionPriority.High.Value, Enum.KeyCode.LeftShift)\n\n-- Unbind when no longer needed\nCAS:UnbindAction(\"Sprint\")"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "CAS vs UIS", "text": "<strong>CAS</strong>: gameplay actions (sprint, shoot, interact) — bindable, prioritized, auto mobile buttons<br><strong>UIS</strong>: raw input detection, UI interactions, device queries"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎮 Gamepad Support", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local UIS = game:GetService(\"UserInputService\")\n\n-- Check if gamepad connected\nif UIS.GamepadEnabled then\n    print(\"Gamepad detected!\")\nend\n\n-- Full gamepad input handling\nUIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(input, gpe)\n    if gpe then return end\n\n    if input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Gamepad1 then\n        if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.ButtonA then\n            jump()\n        elseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.ButtonB then\n            dodge()\n        elseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.ButtonX then\n            interact()\n        elseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.ButtonR1 then\n            attack()\n        end\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Read thumbstick continuously\nRunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function()\n    local gamepad = UIS:GetGamepadState(Enum.UserInputType.Gamepad1)\n    for _, input in gamepad do\n        if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.Thumbstick1 then\n            local x = input.Position.X  -- -1 to 1\n            local y = input.Position.Y  -- -1 to 1\n            if math.abs(x) > 0.15 or math.abs(y) > 0.15 then\n                moveCharacter(x, y) -- deadzone filtered\n            end\n        elseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.ButtonR2 then\n            local trigger = input.Position.Z -- 0 to 1\n            setThrottle(trigger)\n        end\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Haptic feedback (vibration)\nlocal HapticService = game:GetService(\"HapticService\")\nif HapticService:IsVibrationSupported(Enum.UserInputType.Gamepad1) then\n    HapticService:SetMotor(Enum.UserInputType.Gamepad1,\n        Enum.VibrationMotor.Large, 0.5) -- 50% intensity\n    task.wait(0.2)\n    HapticService:SetMotor(Enum.UserInputType.Gamepad1,\n        Enum.VibrationMotor.Large, 0)\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📱 Mobile & Cross-Platform Input", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Detect platform\nlocal function getPlatform(): string\n    if UIS.TouchEnabled and not UIS.KeyboardEnabled then\n        return \"mobile\"\n    elseif UIS.GamepadEnabled and not UIS.KeyboardEnabled then\n        return \"console\"\n    else\n        return \"pc\"\n    end\nend\n\n-- Custom drag-and-drop system\nlocal function makeDraggable(guiElement: GuiObject)\n    local dragging = false\n    local dragStart, startPos\n\n    guiElement.InputBegan:Connect(function(input)\n        if input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton1\n        or input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch then\n            dragging = true\n            dragStart = input.Position\n            startPos = guiElement.Position\n        end\n    end)\n\n    UIS.InputChanged:Connect(function(input)\n        if not dragging then return end\n        if input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseMovement\n        or input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch then\n            local delta = input.Position - dragStart\n            guiElement.Position = UDim2.new(\n                startPos.X.Scale, startPos.X.Offset + delta.X,\n                startPos.Y.Scale, startPos.Y.Offset + delta.Y\n            )\n        end\n    end)\n\n    UIS.InputEnded:Connect(function(input)\n        if input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton1\n        or input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch then\n            dragging = false\n        end\n    end)\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⌨️ Key Combo Detection", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Detect key combinations (Ctrl+Shift+Z etc.)\nlocal heldKeys = {}\n\nUIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(input, gpe)\n    if gpe then return end\n    heldKeys[input.KeyCode] = true\nend)\n\nUIS.InputEnded:Connect(function(input)\n    heldKeys[input.KeyCode] = nil\nend)\n\nlocal function isCombo(...: Enum.KeyCode): boolean\n    for _, key in {...} do\n        if not heldKeys[key] then return false end\n    end\n    return true\nend\n\n-- Usage\nUIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(input, gpe)\n    if gpe then return end\n    if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.Z\n       and isCombo(Enum.KeyCode.LeftControl, Enum.KeyCode.LeftShift)\n    then\n        undo()\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Sequential combo (Konami code style)\nlocal comboSequence = {\n    Enum.KeyCode.Up, Enum.KeyCode.Up,\n    Enum.KeyCode.Down, Enum.KeyCode.Down,\n    Enum.KeyCode.Left, Enum.KeyCode.Right,\n}\nlocal comboIndex = 1\nlocal lastInputTime = 0\n\nUIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(input, gpe)\n    if gpe then return end\n    if tick() - lastInputTime > 2 then comboIndex = 1 end\n    lastInputTime = tick()\n\n    if input.KeyCode == comboSequence[comboIndex] then\n        comboIndex += 1\n        if comboIndex > #comboSequence then\n            comboIndex = 1\n            print(\"SECRET COMBO ACTIVATED!\")\n        end\n    else\n        comboIndex = 1\n    end\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Focus Management", "text": "Use <code>UIS:GetFocusedTextBox()</code> to check if a TextBox is focused. Don't process gameplay input when the player is typing."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "Why is ContextActionService preferred over UserInputService for gameplay actions?", "options": [{"text": "It's faster", "correct": false}, {"text": "It auto-creates mobile buttons and supports priority binding", "correct": true}, {"text": "It works on the server", "correct": false}, {"text": "It detects all input types", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! CAS supports auto mobile buttons, action priorities, and clean bind/unbind.", "incorrect": "CAS auto-creates <strong>mobile buttons</strong> and supports <strong>priority stacking</strong> for action overrides."}}, {"id": 32, "title": "CollectionService", "icon": "🏷️", "color": "#38bdf8", "desc": "Tag-based systems, component pattern, lifecycle management, and practical implementations", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🏷️ Tagging Basics", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>CollectionService</strong> lets you attach <strong>tags</strong> (string labels) to any Instance. This enables powerful data-driven game design where behavior is defined by tags, not script hierarchy."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local CS = game:GetService(\"CollectionService\")\n\n-- Add/remove tags\nCS:AddTag(part, \"Lava\")\nCS:AddTag(part, \"DamageZone\")\nCS:RemoveTag(part, \"Lava\")\n\n-- Check tags\nCS:HasTag(part, \"Lava\")          -- boolean\nCS:GetTags(part)                 -- {\"DamageZone\"}\n\n-- Get all instances with a tag\nlocal allLava = CS:GetTagged(\"Lava\")\nfor _, lavaPart in allLava do\n    lavaPart.BrickColor = BrickColor.new(\"Bright red\")\nend\n\n-- Listen for tag additions/removals (CRITICAL for dynamic objects)\nCS:GetInstanceAddedSignal(\"Lava\"):Connect(function(inst)\n    print(inst.Name, \"became lava!\")\n    setupLava(inst)\nend)\n\nCS:GetInstanceRemovedSignal(\"Lava\"):Connect(function(inst)\n    print(inst.Name, \"no longer lava!\")\n    cleanupLava(inst)\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Studio Tagging", "text": "You can add tags in Studio using the <strong>Properties panel > Tags section</strong> or the <strong>Tag Editor</strong> plugin. No scripting required!"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🧩 Component Pattern", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "The <strong>Component Pattern</strong> attaches reusable behavior to any tagged Instance. It's the foundation of scalable Roblox game architecture."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Generic component manager\nlocal function createComponent(tag: string, config: {\n    init: (Instance) -> any,\n    cleanup: ((Instance, any) -> ())?,\n})\n    local CS = game:GetService(\"CollectionService\")\n    local instances = {} -- instance -> component data\n\n    local function setup(inst: Instance)\n        if instances[inst] then return end\n        instances[inst] = config.init(inst)\n    end\n\n    local function teardown(inst: Instance)\n        if not instances[inst] then return end\n        if config.cleanup then\n            config.cleanup(inst, instances[inst])\n        end\n        instances[inst] = nil\n    end\n\n    -- Handle existing + future tagged instances\n    for _, inst in CS:GetTagged(tag) do\n        task.defer(setup, inst)\n    end\n    CS:GetInstanceAddedSignal(tag):Connect(setup)\n    CS:GetInstanceRemovedSignal(tag):Connect(teardown)\n\n    return instances\nend\n\n-- Example: \"Lava\" component\ncreateComponent(\"Lava\", {\n    init = function(part)\n        local conn = part.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\n            local hum = hit.Parent:FindFirstChildOfClass(\"Humanoid\")\n            if hum then hum:TakeDamage(25) end\n        end)\n        return { connection = conn }\n    end,\n    cleanup = function(part, data)\n        data.connection:Disconnect()\n    end,\n})\n\n-- Example: \"Spinner\" component\ncreateComponent(\"Spinner\", {\n    init = function(part)\n        local conn = RunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function(dt)\n            part.CFrame *= CFrame.Angles(0, math.rad(90) * dt, 0)\n        end)\n        return { connection = conn }\n    end,\n    cleanup = function(part, data)\n        data.connection:Disconnect()\n    end,\n})"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎮 Practical Tag Systems", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Interactable system: \"Interactable\" tag\ncreateComponent(\"Interactable\", {\n    init = function(inst)\n        local prompt = Instance.new(\"ProximityPrompt\")\n        prompt.ObjectText = inst:GetAttribute(\"Label\") or inst.Name\n        prompt.ActionText = inst:GetAttribute(\"Action\") or \"Interact\"\n        prompt.MaxActivationDistance = inst:GetAttribute(\"Range\") or 10\n        prompt.Parent = inst\n\n        local conn = prompt.Triggered:Connect(function(player)\n            local handler = inst:GetAttribute(\"Handler\")\n            if handler then\n                -- Fire a BindableEvent named after the handler\n                local event = RS:FindFirstChild(handler)\n                if event then event:Fire(player, inst) end\n            end\n        end)\n        return { prompt = prompt, connection = conn }\n    end,\n    cleanup = function(inst, data)\n        data.connection:Disconnect()\n        data.prompt:Destroy()\n    end,\n})\n\n-- Collectible system: \"Collectible\" tag\ncreateComponent(\"Collectible\", {\n    init = function(part)\n        local originalCF = part.CFrame\n        local debounce = false\n\n        -- Floating animation\n        local hbConn = RunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()\n            local t = tick()\n            part.CFrame = originalCF\n                * CFrame.new(0, math.sin(t * 2) * 0.5, 0)\n                * CFrame.Angles(0, t, 0)\n        end)\n\n        local touchConn = part.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\n            if debounce then return end\n            local player = Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(hit.Parent)\n            if not player then return end\n            debounce = true\n            collectRemote:FireClient(player, part:GetAttribute(\"Type\"))\n            part:Destroy()\n        end)\n\n        return { connections = {hbConn, touchConn} }\n    end,\n    cleanup = function(part, data)\n        for _, c in data.connections do c:Disconnect() end\n    end,\n})"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What signal fires when a new Instance receives a specific tag at runtime?", "options": [{"text": "CollectionService.TagAdded", "correct": false}, {"text": "CollectionService:GetInstanceAddedSignal(tag)", "correct": true}, {"text": "Instance:GetAttributeChangedSignal()", "correct": false}, {"text": "workspace.DescendantAdded", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! <code>GetInstanceAddedSignal(tag)</code> fires for each new Instance receiving that tag.", "incorrect": "Use <code>GetInstanceAddedSignal(tagName)</code> to react to new tagged instances."}}, {"id": 33, "title": "PhysicsService & Constraints", "icon": "⚙️", "color": "#ffb86c", "desc": "Collision groups, constraints deep dive, ragdolls, vehicle physics, and simulation", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🛡️ Collision Groups", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Collision groups</strong> control which objects physically collide. Essential for player-projectile pass-through, NPC-NPC separation, and ghost effects."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local PS = game:GetService(\"PhysicsService\")\n\n-- Register groups\nPS:RegisterCollisionGroup(\"Players\")\nPS:RegisterCollisionGroup(\"Enemies\")\nPS:RegisterCollisionGroup(\"Projectiles\")\nPS:RegisterCollisionGroup(\"Ragdolls\")\n\n-- Configure collisions\nPS:CollisionGroupSetCollidable(\"Players\", \"Projectiles\", false)\nPS:CollisionGroupSetCollidable(\"Players\", \"Players\", false)\nPS:CollisionGroupSetCollidable(\"Projectiles\", \"Enemies\", true)\nPS:CollisionGroupSetCollidable(\"Ragdolls\", \"Players\", false)\n\n-- Assign parts to groups\nlocal function setCollisionGroup(model: Model, group: string)\n    for _, part in model:GetDescendants() do\n        if part:IsA(\"BasePart\") then\n            part.CollisionGroup = group\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n-- Usage: on character spawn\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\n    player.CharacterAdded:Connect(function(char)\n        setCollisionGroup(char, \"Players\")\n    end)\nend)\n\n-- Projectile ignores players\nlocal bullet = Instance.new(\"Part\")\nbullet.CollisionGroup = \"Projectiles\"\nbullet.Size = Vector3.new(0.3, 0.3, 1)\nbullet.Parent = workspace"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔧 Constraints Deep Dive", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- HingeConstraint: doors, rotating platforms\nlocal hinge = Instance.new(\"HingeConstraint\")\nhinge.ActuatorType = Enum.ActuatorType.Motor\nhinge.MotorMaxTorque = 1000\nhinge.AngularVelocity = 2  -- rad/s\nhinge.Parent = doorHinge\n\n-- SpringConstraint: suspension, bouncy platforms\nlocal spring = Instance.new(\"SpringConstraint\")\nspring.Stiffness = 500\nspring.Damping = 20\nspring.FreeLength = 5\nspring.Parent = attachment\n\n-- RopeConstraint: swinging, hanging objects\nlocal rope = Instance.new(\"RopeConstraint\")\nrope.Length = 15\nrope.Restitution = 0.3  -- bounciness\nrope.Parent = attachment\n\n-- PrismaticConstraint: elevators, sliding doors\nlocal prismatic = Instance.new(\"PrismaticConstraint\")\nprismatic.ActuatorType = Enum.ActuatorType.Servo\nprismatic.Speed = 10\nprismatic.TargetPosition = 20\nprismatic.Parent = attachment\n\n-- AlignPosition: smooth following (NPCs, floating objects)\nlocal align = Instance.new(\"AlignPosition\")\nalign.MaxForce = 50000\nalign.MaxVelocity = 30\nalign.Responsiveness = 25\nalign.Parent = part\n\n-- AlignOrientation: face a target\nlocal orient = Instance.new(\"AlignOrientation\")\norient.MaxTorque = 50000\norient.Responsiveness = 25\norient.Parent = part"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Constraint", "Use Case"], "rows": [["HingeConstraint", "Doors, wheels, rotating platforms"], ["SpringConstraint", "Suspension, bounce pads"], ["RopeConstraint", "Swings, hanging decorations"], ["PrismaticConstraint", "Elevators, sliding mechanisms"], ["BallSocketConstraint", "Ragdoll joints, chains"], ["AlignPosition", "Smooth NPC movement, floating items"], ["AlignOrientation", "Face targets, turret tracking"], ["LinearVelocity", "Conveyor belts, constant force"], ["AngularVelocity", "Spinning objects, propellers"], ["VectorForce", "Gravity modifiers, jetpacks"]]}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🪶 Ragdoll System", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local function ragdollCharacter(character: Model)\n    local humanoid = character:FindFirstChildOfClass(\"Humanoid\")\n    if not humanoid then return end\n\n    humanoid:ChangeState(Enum.HumanoidStateType.Physics)\n\n    for _, joint in character:GetDescendants() do\n        if joint:IsA(\"Motor6D\") then\n            -- Replace Motor6D with BallSocket\n            local socket = Instance.new(\"BallSocketConstraint\")\n            socket.LimitsEnabled = true\n            socket.TwistLimitsEnabled = true\n            socket.UpperAngle = 45\n            socket.TwistLowerAngle = -45\n            socket.TwistUpperAngle = 45\n\n            -- Create attachments at joint position\n            local a0 = Instance.new(\"Attachment\")\n            a0.CFrame = joint.C0\n            a0.Parent = joint.Part0\n\n            local a1 = Instance.new(\"Attachment\")\n            a1.CFrame = joint.C1\n            a1.Parent = joint.Part1\n\n            socket.Attachment0 = a0\n            socket.Attachment1 = a1\n            socket.Parent = joint.Parent\n\n            joint.Enabled = false -- disable Motor6D\n        end\n    end\n\n    -- Unanchor all parts\n    for _, part in character:GetDescendants() do\n        if part:IsA(\"BasePart\") then\n            part.CanCollide = true\n            part.CollisionGroup = \"Ragdolls\"\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n-- Recover from ragdoll\nlocal function unragdoll(character: Model)\n    local humanoid = character:FindFirstChildOfClass(\"Humanoid\")\n    if not humanoid then return end\n\n    for _, desc in character:GetDescendants() do\n        if desc:IsA(\"BallSocketConstraint\") then desc:Destroy() end\n        if desc:IsA(\"Motor6D\") then desc.Enabled = true end\n    end\n\n    humanoid:ChangeState(Enum.HumanoidStateType.GettingUp)\nend"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What does <code>CollisionGroupSetCollidable(\"A\", \"B\", false)</code> do?", "options": [{"text": "Makes A and B always collide", "correct": false}, {"text": "Prevents collision between groups A and B", "correct": true}, {"text": "Removes both collision groups", "correct": false}, {"text": "Makes group A invisible to group B", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Setting collidable to false means objects in groups A and B pass through each other.", "incorrect": "Setting collidable to <strong>false</strong> means groups A and B won't physically collide."}}, {"id": 34, "title": "HttpService", "icon": "🌐", "color": "#4ade80", "desc": "JSON encoding, HTTP requests, webhook integration, API patterns, and rate limiting", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📦 JSON Encode/Decode", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local Http = game:GetService(\"HttpService\")\n\n-- Encode Luau table to JSON string\nlocal data = {\n    playerName = \"Zeeval\",\n    score = 1500,\n    inventory = {\"Sword\", \"Shield\", \"Potion\"},\n    stats = { strength = 25, speed = 18 },\n}\nlocal json = Http:JSONEncode(data)\nprint(json)\n-- {\"playerName\":\"Zeeval\",\"score\":1500,\"inventory\":[\"Sword\",\"Shield\",\"Potion\"],...}\n\n-- Decode JSON string to Luau table\nlocal decoded = Http:JSONDecode(json)\nprint(decoded.playerName) -- \"Zeeval\"\nprint(decoded.inventory[1]) -- \"Sword\"\n\n-- Always wrap in pcall (malformed JSON will error)\nlocal ok, result = pcall(Http.JSONDecode, Http, userInput)\nif ok then\n    print(\"Valid JSON:\", result)\nelse\n    warn(\"Invalid JSON:\", result)\nend\n\n-- Generate unique IDs\nlocal guid = Http:GenerateGUID(false) -- no curly braces\nprint(guid) -- \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890\"\n\n-- URL encoding\nlocal encoded = Http:UrlEncode(\"hello world & more\")\nprint(encoded) -- \"hello%20world%20%26%20more\""}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "Enable HTTP Requests", "text": "You must enable <strong>Allow HTTP Requests</strong> in Game Settings > Security before <code>:RequestAsync</code> works."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🚀 HTTP Requests", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- GET request\nlocal function httpGet(url: string): (boolean, any)\n    local ok, result = pcall(function()\n        return Http:RequestAsync({\n            Url = url,\n            Method = \"GET\",\n            Headers = {\n                [\"Accept\"] = \"application/json\",\n            },\n        })\n    end)\n\n    if ok and result.Success then\n        return true, Http:JSONDecode(result.Body)\n    end\n    return false, ok and result.StatusCode or result\nend\n\n-- POST request\nlocal function httpPost(url: string, body: {}): (boolean, any)\n    local ok, result = pcall(function()\n        return Http:RequestAsync({\n            Url = url,\n            Method = \"POST\",\n            Headers = {\n                [\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\",\n            },\n            Body = Http:JSONEncode(body),\n        })\n    end)\n\n    if ok and result.Success then\n        local bodyOk, decoded = pcall(Http.JSONDecode, Http, result.Body)\n        return true, bodyOk and decoded or result.Body\n    end\n    return false, ok and result.StatusMessage or result\nend\n\n-- Response object structure:\n-- { Success: bool, StatusCode: number,\n--   StatusMessage: string, Headers: {}, Body: string }"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📣 Discord Webhook Integration", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Send events to Discord\nlocal WEBHOOK_URL = \"https://discord.com/api/webhooks/YOUR_WEBHOOK\"\n\nlocal function sendToDiscord(content: string, embed: {}?)\n    local payload = { content = content }\n\n    if embed then\n        payload.content = nil\n        payload.embeds = {{\n            title = embed.title,\n            description = embed.description,\n            color = embed.color or 5814783, -- teal\n            fields = embed.fields or {},\n            timestamp = DateTime.now():ToIsoDate(),\n            footer = { text = \"Game Server\" },\n        }}\n    end\n\n    task.spawn(function()\n        pcall(Http.RequestAsync, Http, {\n            Url = WEBHOOK_URL,\n            Method = \"POST\",\n            Headers = {[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"},\n            Body = Http:JSONEncode(payload),\n        })\n    end)\nend\n\n-- Usage examples\nsendToDiscord(nil, {\n    title = \"Player Joined\",\n    description = player.Name .. \" joined the server!\",\n    color = 5763719, -- green\n    fields = {\n        {name = \"Players\", value = tostring(#Players:GetPlayers()), inline = true},\n        {name = \"Server ID\", value = game.JobId:sub(1,8), inline = true},\n    },\n})"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "danger", "title": "Security", "text": "<strong>NEVER</strong> put webhook URLs in client scripts! Always use server scripts. Leaked webhooks can be abused for spam."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔄 Retry & Rate Limiting", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Retry with exponential backoff\nlocal function httpRetry(requestFn, maxRetries: number)\n    maxRetries = maxRetries or 3\n    local delay = 1\n\n    for attempt = 1, maxRetries do\n        local ok, result = pcall(requestFn)\n        if ok then return true, result end\n\n        warn(\"HTTP attempt\", attempt, \"failed:\", result)\n        if attempt < maxRetries then\n            task.wait(delay)\n            delay *= 2 -- exponential backoff\n        end\n    end\n    return false, \"Max retries exceeded\"\nend\n\n-- Rate limiter for outgoing requests\nlocal RateLimiter = {}\nRateLimiter.__index = RateLimiter\n\nfunction RateLimiter.new(maxPerMinute: number)\n    return setmetatable({\n        max = maxPerMinute,\n        timestamps = {},\n    }, RateLimiter)\nend\n\nfunction RateLimiter:canRequest(): boolean\n    local now = tick()\n    -- Remove timestamps older than 60s\n    while #self.timestamps > 0 and now - self.timestamps[1] > 60 do\n        table.remove(self.timestamps, 1)\n    end\n    return #self.timestamps < self.max\nend\n\nfunction RateLimiter:record()\n    table.insert(self.timestamps, tick())\nend\n\n-- Roblox limit: 500 HTTP requests/min\nlocal limiter = RateLimiter.new(450) -- safety margin\n\nlocal function safeRequest(url)\n    if not limiter:canRequest() then\n        warn(\"Rate limited!\")\n        return false\n    end\n    limiter:record()\n    return httpGet(url)\nend"}, {"type": "table", "headers": ["Limit", "Value"], "rows": [["Requests per minute", "500"], ["Request body size", "1 MB"], ["Response body size", "1 MB"], ["Blocked domains", "roblox.com, robloxlabs.com"], ["Timeout", "30 seconds"]]}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What must be enabled in Game Settings for <code>HttpService:RequestAsync</code> to work?", "options": [{"text": "API Services", "correct": false}, {"text": "Allow HTTP Requests", "correct": true}, {"text": "Enable Studio Access", "correct": false}, {"text": "Third Party Sales", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! You must enable <strong>Allow HTTP Requests</strong> in Game Settings > Security.", "incorrect": "<strong>Allow HTTP Requests</strong> must be toggled on in Game Settings > Security."}}, {"id": 35, "title": "MemoryStoreService", "icon": "🧠", "color": "#a78bfa", "desc": "Sorted maps, queues, hash maps, cross-server communication, and matchmaking", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "📊 Sorted Maps", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>MemoryStoreService</strong> provides fast, temporary, cross-server data storage. Data expires automatically (max 45 days). Unlike DataStores, it's designed for <strong>real-time, ephemeral</strong> data."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local MSS = game:GetService(\"MemoryStoreService\")\n\n-- Sorted Map: key-value store with sorting\nlocal leaderMap = MSS:GetSortedMap(\"LiveLeaderboard\")\n\n-- Set with expiration (seconds)\nleaderMap:SetAsync(\"user_12345\", 1500, 3600) -- expires in 1 hour\n\n-- Get a single key\nlocal ok, score = pcall(leaderMap.GetAsync, leaderMap, \"user_12345\")\n\n-- Get range (sorted by key or by sort key)\nlocal ok, entries = pcall(function()\n    return leaderMap:GetRangeAsync(\n        Enum.SortDirection.Descending, -- direction\n        50                              -- count\n    )\nend)\n\nif ok then\n    for rank, entry in entries do\n        print(rank, entry.key, entry.value)\n    end\nend\n\n-- Update atomically\nleaderMap:UpdateAsync(\"user_12345\", function(old)\n    return (old or 0) + 100 -- add 100 points\nend, 3600)\n\n-- Remove\nleaderMap:RemoveAsync(\"user_12345\")"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📨 Queues", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>MemoryStore Queues</strong> are FIFO (first-in-first-out) structures perfect for matchmaking, job processing, and cross-server task distribution."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local queue = MSS:GetQueue(\"MatchmakingQueue\", 30) -- 30s invisibility\n\n-- Add to queue (with priority and expiration)\nqueue:AddAsync(\"player_data_here\", 300, 5)\n-- args: value, expiration (sec), priority (higher = first)\n\n-- Read from queue (server-side worker)\nlocal function processQueue()\n    while true do\n        local ok, result = pcall(function()\n            return queue:ReadAsync(1, false, 5)\n            -- count, allOrNothing, waitTimeout\n        end)\n\n        if ok and #result > 0 then\n            local item = result[1]\n            print(\"Processing:\", item.value)\n\n            -- After processing, remove it\n            pcall(queue.RemoveAsync, queue, item.id)\n        else\n            task.wait(1) -- no items, wait\n        end\n    end\nend\n\ntask.spawn(processQueue)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎮 Cross-Server Matchmaking", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local MSS = game:GetService(\"MemoryStoreService\")\nlocal TeleportService = game:GetService(\"TeleportService\")\n\nlocal matchQueue = MSS:GetSortedMap(\"MatchQueue\")\nlocal MATCH_SIZE = 4\nlocal MATCH_TIMEOUT = 120\n\n-- Player requests to join matchmaking\nlocal function joinMatchmaking(player: Player)\n    local entry = {\n        userId = player.UserId,\n        name = player.Name,\n        skill = getPlayerSkill(player),\n        serverId = game.JobId,\n        timestamp = os.time(),\n    }\n    pcall(matchQueue.SetAsync, matchQueue,\n        \"player_\" .. player.UserId,\n        entry,\n        MATCH_TIMEOUT\n    )\nend\n\n-- Server-side: check for enough players\nlocal function tryFormMatch()\n    local ok, entries = pcall(function()\n        return matchQueue:GetRangeAsync(\n            Enum.SortDirection.Ascending, MATCH_SIZE * 2\n        )\n    end)\n    if not ok or #entries < MATCH_SIZE then return end\n\n    -- Group by similar skill\n    local group = {}\n    for _, entry in entries do\n        table.insert(group, entry.value)\n        if #group >= MATCH_SIZE then break end\n    end\n\n    -- Reserve a server and teleport\n    local code = TeleportService:ReserveServer(MATCH_PLACE_ID)\n    local players = {}\n    for _, data in group do\n        local p = Players:GetPlayerByUserId(data.userId)\n        if p then table.insert(players, p) end\n        pcall(matchQueue.RemoveAsync, matchQueue,\n            \"player_\" .. data.userId)\n    end\n\n    if #players >= 2 then\n        TeleportService:TeleportToPrivateServer(\n            MATCH_PLACE_ID, code, players\n        )\n    end\nend\n\n-- Run match check every few seconds\ntask.spawn(function()\n    while true do\n        task.wait(3)\n        pcall(tryFormMatch)\n    end\nend)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📋 Limits & Best Practices", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Property", "Limit"], "rows": [["Item expiration", "10 sec – 45 days"], ["Key size", "128 bytes"], ["Value size", "32 KB"], ["Sorted map items", "No hard limit (budget-based)"], ["Request rate", "1000 + 100×players /min per partition"], ["Queue read visibility", "30 sec default"]]}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Best Practices:</strong><ul><li>Always set reasonable <strong>expiration times</strong> — MemoryStore has limited capacity</li><li>Use <strong>UpdateAsync</strong> for atomic operations (avoid read-then-write races)</li><li>Handle <strong>pcall failures</strong> — MemoryStore can throttle under load</li><li>Prefer <strong>Sorted Maps</strong> for key-value lookups, <strong>Queues</strong> for task processing</li><li>Don't store data that needs persistence — use DataStores for that</li><li>MemoryStore is <strong>cross-server</strong> by default — all servers in the same game share it</li></ul>"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "MemoryStore vs DataStore", "text": "<strong>DataStore:</strong> permanent, disk-based, higher latency, lower throughput<br><strong>MemoryStore:</strong> temporary, RAM-based, lower latency, higher throughput"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What happens to MemoryStore data when its expiration time passes?", "options": [{"text": "It persists forever", "correct": false}, {"text": "It moves to a DataStore", "correct": false}, {"text": "It is automatically deleted", "correct": true}, {"text": "It triggers an event", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! MemoryStore data is <strong>automatically deleted</strong> when the expiration time passes.", "incorrect": "MemoryStore data is <strong>ephemeral</strong> — it auto-deletes when the TTL expires."}}, {"id": 36, "title": "Debugging Techniques", "icon": "🐛", "color": "#f87171", "desc": "Finding and fixing bugs with print, warn, breakpoints, and the Developer Console", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🐛 What Is Debugging?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Debugging</strong> is the process of finding and fixing mistakes (\"bugs\") in your code. Even experienced developers spend a huge portion of their time debugging. The good news is Roblox Studio gives you powerful tools to track down problems."}, {"type": "text", "value": "The most common types of bugs are:<br>• <strong>Syntax errors</strong> — Typos or missing keywords. Luau catches these immediately with red underlines.<br>• <strong>Runtime errors</strong> — Code that's valid but crashes when it runs (e.g., trying to access a nil value).<br>• <strong>Logic errors</strong> — Code runs without crashing, but produces the wrong result. These are the hardest to find."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🖨️ print(), warn(), and error()", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "The simplest debugging tool is <code>print()</code>. Sprinkle it through your code to see what's happening at each step."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- print(): general info (white text in Output)\nprint(\"Player health is\", humanoid.Health)\nprint(\"Function reached!\") -- confirm code is running\n\n-- warn(): warnings (yellow text in Output)\nwarn(\"Player data might be nil!\")\nwarn(\"Unexpected value:\", someVar)\n\n-- error(): fatal errors (red text, stops execution)\nerror(\"This should never happen!\")\n\n-- Debugging a function\nlocal function calculateDamage(weapon, target)\n    print(\"calculateDamage called\")         -- Step 1: is it even called?\n    print(\"  weapon:\", weapon)               -- Step 2: are inputs correct?\n    print(\"  target:\", target)\n\n    if not weapon then\n        warn(\"weapon is nil!\")               -- Step 3: handle edge cases\n        return 0\n    end\n\n    local damage = weapon.Damage * (1 - target.Armor/100)\n    print(\"  calculated damage:\", damage)    -- Step 4: is result correct?\n    return damage\nend"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "The 'Print Trail' Technique", "text": "When something isn't working, add <code>print(\"STEP 1\")</code>, <code>print(\"STEP 2\")</code>, etc. through your code. When you run it, you'll see exactly which step it reaches before the bug happens. Then you know where to look!"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔴 Breakpoints & Debugger", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Instead of adding print() everywhere, you can use <strong>breakpoints</strong> — markers that <strong>pause your code</strong> at a specific line so you can inspect everything."}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>How to use breakpoints in Roblox Studio:</strong><br><br><strong>1.</strong> Open your script.<br><strong>2.</strong> Click the <strong>left margin</strong> (gray area) next to a line number. A <strong>red dot</strong> appears — that's your breakpoint.<br><strong>3.</strong> Press <strong>Play</strong>. When execution hits that line, the game <strong>pauses</strong>.<br><strong>4.</strong> Look at the <strong>Watch</strong> and <strong>Locals</strong> panels to see every variable's value.<br><strong>5.</strong> Use the toolbar buttons: <strong>Step Over</strong> (next line), <strong>Step Into</strong> (enter function), <strong>Step Out</strong> (exit function), <strong>Continue</strong> (resume)."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- You can also trigger breakpoints programmatically:\ndebug.setbreakpoint(nil)  -- not commonly used, but exists\n\n-- Conditional breakpoints (right-click the red dot in Studio):\n-- \"Break when: health < 10\"\n-- This pauses ONLY when the condition is true\n\n-- The Watch panel lets you type expressions:\n-- e.g., type \"player.Character.Humanoid.Health\" to see it live\n\n-- Call stack shows you HOW the code got to this point:\n-- functionA() called functionB() called functionC() ← you are here"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Debugger Panels", "text": "Go to <strong>View menu → Debugger</strong> panels: <strong>Watch</strong> (track specific expressions), <strong>Call Stack</strong> (see function call chain), <strong>Breakpoints</strong> (manage all breakpoints). These are invaluable for complex bugs."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📊 Developer Console (F9)", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "The <strong>Developer Console</strong> (press <strong>F9</strong> in Studio or in a live game) shows detailed information about your game's performance and errors."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "text", "code": "Key tabs in the Developer Console:\n\n📋 Log         — All print/warn/error output, filterable by source\n📜 Memory      — RAM usage breakdown by category\n📈 Network     — Remote event traffic and bandwidth\n⚙️ Script Perf — CPU time per script (find slow scripts!)\n🔌 DataStores  — DataStore request logs and errors\n📊 ServerStats — Server FPS, heartbeat, physics time"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Script Performance</strong> is especially useful — it shows exactly how much CPU time each script uses per second. If a script shows high numbers, that's your bottleneck."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔍 Common Errors & How to Fix Them", "content": [{"type": "table", "headers": ["Error Message", "What It Means", "How to Fix"], "rows": [["attempt to index nil", "You're using . or [] on a nil value", "Check that the variable exists: print it first, use if checks"], ["attempt to call a nil value", "You're calling something() that is nil", "Check function name spelling, ensure it's defined before the call"], ["Expected 'end'", "Missing an 'end' keyword", "Every if/for/while/function/do needs a matching 'end'"], ["Expected ')' or ','", "Missing closing parenthesis or comma", "Count your opening and closing parens"], ["Infinite yield possible", "WaitForChild can't find the object", "Check the name spelling, make sure the object exists"], ["ServerScriptService is not accessible", "Client script trying to access server-only location", "Move shared items to ReplicatedStorage"], ["DataStore request was throttled", "Too many DataStore requests", "Add delays between requests, check budget"]]}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Reading Error Messages", "text": "Error messages in Roblox follow this format: <code>ScriptName:LineNumber: error message</code>. Always look at the <strong>line number</strong> first — it tells you exactly where to look. Then read the message to understand <em>what</em> went wrong."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🛠️ Debugging Strategies", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>When something doesn't work, follow this process:</strong>"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>1. Read the error message</strong> — It usually tells you exactly what's wrong and on which line.<br><br><strong>2. Reproduce the bug</strong> — Can you make it happen every time? Understanding <em>when</em> it happens is half the battle.<br><br><strong>3. Isolate the problem</strong> — Comment out code (<code>--</code>) until the error stops. The last thing you uncommented is the culprit.<br><br><strong>4. Check your assumptions</strong> — Add <code>print()</code> to verify that variables hold the values you <em>think</em> they hold. Most bugs come from wrong assumptions.<br><br><strong>5. Rubber duck debugging</strong> — Explain your code line-by-line to someone (or a rubber duck). The act of explaining often reveals the mistake."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Isolating a bug with commenting:\nlocal function onPlayerJoin(player)\n    -- print(\"Step 1: player joined\")\n    local data = loadData(player)  -- does this error?\n    -- print(\"Step 2: data loaded\", data)\n    setupInventory(player, data)   -- or this?\n    -- print(\"Step 3: inventory set up\")\n    applyCosmetics(player, data)   -- or this?\n    -- print(\"Step 4: cosmetics applied\")\nend\n-- Uncomment the prints one by one to find where it breaks!"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "A script crashes with \"attempt to index nil with 'Health'\". What does this mean?", "options": [{"text": "The Health property doesn't exist", "correct": false}, {"text": "You're trying to access .Health on a variable that is nil", "correct": true}, {"text": "Health is set to 0", "correct": false}, {"text": "The script has a syntax error", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! The variable you're indexing with .Health is nil — the object doesn't exist yet or wasn't found.", "incorrect": "\"attempt to index nil\" means you're using <code>.something</code> on a variable that is <code>nil</code>."}}, {"id": 37, "title": "MicroProfiler & Profiling", "icon": "📊", "color": "#38bdf8", "desc": "Studio profiling with MicroProfiler, debug.profilebegin, and optimization workflows", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "⏱️ What Is Profiling?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Profiling</strong> is measuring <em>how long</em> each part of your code takes to run. When your game feels laggy, profiling tells you exactly <em>which</em> code is slow so you can fix it. Without profiling, you're guessing."}, {"type": "text", "value": "Roblox's built-in profiler is called the <strong>MicroProfiler</strong>. It shows a real-time timeline of every task the engine performs each frame — rendering, physics, your scripts, networking, and more."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔬 Opening the MicroProfiler", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Press <strong>Ctrl + F6</strong> (Windows) or <strong>Cmd + F6</strong> (Mac) in Studio while your game is running. A colorful bar chart appears at the top of the screen — that's the MicroProfiler."}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Reading the timeline:</strong><br><br>• Each <strong>column</strong> is one frame (ideally ~16ms for 60 FPS).<br>• Each <strong>colored bar</strong> is a task. Wider bars = more time spent.<br>• <strong>Hover</strong> over any bar to see its label, duration, and call stack.<br>• Press <strong>Pause</strong> to freeze the timeline and inspect individual frames.<br>• Click a bar to see its <strong>detailed breakdown</strong>."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "text", "code": "Key labels you'll see in the MicroProfiler:\n\nHeartbeat           — Your game logic (RunService.Heartbeat)\nStepped             — Pre-physics logic\nRenderStepped       — Client rendering logic (client only)\nphysicsSteppedTotal — Physics simulation\nRender/Present      — GPU rendering\nnetworkSend/Receive — Network traffic\nLuaGC               — Lua garbage collection\nReplication         — Property replication to clients"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "Frame Budget", "text": "For <strong>60 FPS</strong>, each frame must complete in <strong>16.67ms</strong>. For <strong>30 FPS</strong>, it's <strong>33.3ms</strong>. If your Heartbeat scripts take 10ms, that leaves only 6.67ms for everything else. The MicroProfiler makes this budget visible."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏷️ Custom Profiling Labels", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "You can add your own labels to the MicroProfiler using <code>debug.profilebegin()</code> and <code>debug.profileend()</code>. This lets you see exactly how long <em>your</em> functions take."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "local function updateAllEnemies(enemies)\n    debug.profilebegin(\"UpdateEnemies\")  -- start timing\n\n    for _, enemy in enemies do\n        debug.profilebegin(\"AI_Think\")    -- nested label\n        thinkAI(enemy)\n        debug.profileend()                -- end \"AI_Think\"\n\n        debug.profilebegin(\"AI_Move\")\n        moveEnemy(enemy)\n        debug.profileend()\n    end\n\n    debug.profileend()  -- end \"UpdateEnemies\"\nend\n\n-- These labels appear as colored bars in the MicroProfiler!\n-- You can see: \"UpdateEnemies took 4.2ms, of which\n--   AI_Think was 2.8ms and AI_Move was 1.4ms\"\n\n-- Reusable profiling wrapper\nlocal function profile(label: string, fn: () -> ())\n    debug.profilebegin(label)\n    fn()\n    debug.profileend()\nend\n\n-- Usage:\nprofile(\"PhysicsUpdate\", function()\n    -- expensive code here\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "warn", "title": "Always Match Begin/End", "text": "Every <code>debug.profilebegin()</code> needs a matching <code>debug.profileend()</code>. If you forget one, the profiler timeline will be corrupted. Use the wrapper function pattern above to avoid mistakes."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📈 Detailed Profiling Mode", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Press <strong>Ctrl + P</strong> while the MicroProfiler is open to enter <strong>Detailed Mode</strong>. This gives you:"}, {"type": "text", "value": "• <strong>Frame summary</strong> — Total frame time breakdown by category<br>• <strong>Flame graph</strong> — Hierarchical view showing which functions call which<br>• <strong>Sort by duration</strong> — Find the slowest function instantly<br>• <strong>Export data</strong> — Save profiling data to a file for later analysis"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Benchmarking a function with os.clock()\nlocal function benchmark(label, fn, iterations)\n    iterations = iterations or 1000\n    local start = os.clock()\n    for i = 1, iterations do\n        fn()\n    end\n    local elapsed = os.clock() - start\n    print(`{label}: {elapsed:.4f}s total, {elapsed/iterations*1000:.4f}ms avg`)\nend\n\n-- Compare two approaches:\nbenchmark(\"table.insert\", function()\n    local t = {}\n    for i = 1, 100 do table.insert(t, i) end\nend)\n\nbenchmark(\"direct index\", function()\n    local t = table.create(100)\n    for i = 1, 100 do t[i] = i end\nend)\n-- Result: direct indexing with table.create is faster!"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📋 Script Performance Widget", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Beyond the MicroProfiler, Roblox Studio has a <strong>Script Performance</strong> widget that shows CPU usage per script."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "text", "code": "How to use Script Performance:\n\n1. Go to View → Script Performance\n2. Sort by \"Activity\" (CPU time) column\n3. Look for scripts using > 1% of frame time\n4. Click a script to see which functions are expensive\n5. Optimize the top offenders first\n\nCommon bottlenecks:\n- GetDescendants() called every frame → cache the results\n- Raycast in RenderStepped → throttle to every N frames\n- String concatenation in loops → use table.concat\n- FindFirstChild deep searches → cache references\n- Touched events without debounce → add cooldowns"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "The 80/20 Rule", "text": "Usually, <strong>80% of your lag</strong> comes from <strong>20% of your code</strong>. Profile first, find the actual bottleneck, <em>then</em> optimize. Don't guess — measure! Premature optimization wastes time."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔧 Optimization Workflow", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Step-by-step optimization process:</strong>"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>1. Notice a problem</strong> — FPS drops, lag spikes, slow loading.<br><br><strong>2. Profile</strong> — Open MicroProfiler (Ctrl+F6) and Script Performance. Don't optimize blindly.<br><br><strong>3. Identify the bottleneck</strong> — Which script/function takes the most time?<br><br><strong>4. Understand why</strong> — Is it running too often? Processing too much data? Allocating too many objects?<br><br><strong>5. Fix it</strong> — Cache values, reduce frequency, use spatial indexing, object pool, etc.<br><br><strong>6. Verify</strong> — Profile again. Did the fix help? Sometimes \"optimizations\" make things worse!"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Example optimization: spatial query caching\n\n-- BEFORE (slow): checking distance to every player every frame\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()\n    for _, enemy in workspace.Enemies:GetChildren() do\n        for _, player in Players:GetPlayers() do\n            if player.Character then\n                local dist = (enemy.Position - player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.Position).Magnitude\n                if dist < 50 then\n                    -- chase player\n                end\n            end\n        end\n    end\nend)\n\n-- AFTER (fast): use spatial query, throttle updates\nlocal lastUpdate = 0\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()\n    if tick() - lastUpdate < 0.2 then return end  -- 5x/sec, not 60x\n    lastUpdate = tick()\n\n    for _, enemy in workspace.Enemies:GetChildren() do\n        local nearby = workspace:GetPartBoundsInRadius(\n            enemy.Position, 50, playerParams\n        )\n        if #nearby > 0 then\n            -- chase nearest\n        end\n    end\nend)"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What keyboard shortcut opens the MicroProfiler in Roblox Studio?", "options": [{"text": "F9", "correct": false}, {"text": "Ctrl + F6", "correct": true}, {"text": "Ctrl + P", "correct": false}, {"text": "F12", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Ctrl + F6 (or Cmd + F6 on Mac) toggles the MicroProfiler.", "incorrect": "The MicroProfiler opens with <strong>Ctrl + F6</strong>. F9 opens the Developer Console."}}, {"id": 38, "title": "Unit Testing in Luau", "icon": "🧪", "color": "#4ade80", "desc": "TestEZ patterns, writing testable code, mocking services, and test-driven development", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🧪 Why Test Your Code?", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Unit testing</strong> means writing small scripts that automatically check if your code works correctly. Instead of manually testing every feature by playing your game, you write tests that do it for you in seconds."}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>Benefits:</strong><br>• Catch bugs <em>before</em> they reach players<br>• Refactor code confidently — if tests pass, nothing broke<br>• Document how your code is supposed to work<br>• Save hours of manual testing over a project's lifetime"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "When to Write Tests", "text": "Test <strong>logic and calculations</strong> (damage formulas, inventory management, matchmaking). Don't test Roblox engine behavior (physics, rendering) — that's Roblox's job."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📐 TestEZ Framework", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "<strong>TestEZ</strong> is Roblox's official testing framework (used internally). It uses a <code>describe/it/expect</code> pattern similar to Jest or Mocha from the JavaScript world."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Install: Get TestEZ from github.com/Roblox/testez\n-- Place it in ReplicatedStorage\n\n-- Example test file: MathUtils.spec.lua\nreturn function()\n    local MathUtils = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.Shared.MathUtils)\n\n    describe(\"MathUtils\", function()\n\n        describe(\"lerp\", function()\n            it(\"should return start when t=0\", function()\n                expect(MathUtils.lerp(0, 100, 0)).to.equal(0)\n            end)\n\n            it(\"should return end when t=1\", function()\n                expect(MathUtils.lerp(0, 100, 1)).to.equal(100)\n            end)\n\n            it(\"should return midpoint when t=0.5\", function()\n                expect(MathUtils.lerp(0, 100, 0.5)).to.equal(50)\n            end)\n\n            it(\"should work with negative numbers\", function()\n                expect(MathUtils.lerp(-10, 10, 0.5)).to.equal(0)\n            end)\n        end)\n\n        describe(\"clamp\", function()\n            it(\"should clamp above max\", function()\n                expect(MathUtils.clamp(150, 0, 100)).to.equal(100)\n            end)\n\n            it(\"should clamp below min\", function()\n                expect(MathUtils.clamp(-5, 0, 100)).to.equal(0)\n            end)\n\n            it(\"should return value when in range\", function()\n                expect(MathUtils.clamp(50, 0, 100)).to.equal(50)\n            end)\n        end)\n    end)\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "✅ Assertion Patterns", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- TestEZ expect() API:\nexpect(value).to.equal(expected)           -- strict equality\nexpect(value).to.be.ok()                   -- truthy (not nil, not false)\nexpect(value).to.be.a(\"string\")            -- type check\nexpect(value).to.be.near(3.14, 0.01)       -- float comparison with epsilon\nexpect(fn).to.throw()                      -- expect an error\nexpect(fn).to.throw(\"specific message\")    -- expect specific error\nexpect(value).never.to.equal(other)        -- negation\n\n-- Example: testing an inventory module\nreturn function()\n    local Inventory = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.Shared.Inventory)\n\n    describe(\"Inventory\", function()\n        local inv\n\n        beforeEach(function()\n            inv = Inventory.new(10)  -- 10 slots\n        end)\n\n        it(\"should start empty\", function()\n            expect(inv:getCount()).to.equal(0)\n        end)\n\n        it(\"should add items\", function()\n            local ok = inv:addItem(\"Sword\", 1)\n            expect(ok).to.equal(true)\n            expect(inv:getCount()).to.equal(1)\n            expect(inv:hasItem(\"Sword\")).to.equal(true)\n        end)\n\n        it(\"should reject when full\", function()\n            for i = 1, 10 do\n                inv:addItem(\"Item\" .. i, 1)\n            end\n            local ok = inv:addItem(\"Extra\", 1)\n            expect(ok).to.equal(false)\n            expect(inv:getCount()).to.equal(10)\n        end)\n\n        it(\"should remove items\", function()\n            inv:addItem(\"Sword\", 3)\n            inv:removeItem(\"Sword\", 1)\n            expect(inv:getItemCount(\"Sword\")).to.equal(2)\n        end)\n    end)\nend"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎭 Writing Testable Code", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "The key to testing is writing code that <strong>separates logic from Roblox APIs</strong>. If your damage formula is buried inside a Touched event, it's hard to test. Extract it into a pure function."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- ❌ BAD: Logic mixed with Roblox APIs (hard to test)\npart.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\n    local hum = hit.Parent:FindFirstChildOfClass(\"Humanoid\")\n    if hum then\n        local baseDmg = weapon:GetAttribute(\"Damage\")\n        local armor = hum:GetAttribute(\"Armor\") or 0\n        local finalDmg = baseDmg * (1 - armor / 100)\n        finalDmg = math.max(1, math.floor(finalDmg))\n        hum:TakeDamage(finalDmg)\n    end\nend)\n\n-- ✅ GOOD: Logic extracted into testable function\nlocal Combat = {}\n\nfunction Combat.calculateDamage(baseDamage: number, armor: number): number\n    local reduction = 1 - math.clamp(armor, 0, 100) / 100\n    return math.max(1, math.floor(baseDamage * reduction))\nend\n\nreturn Combat\n\n-- Now test it easily:\nit(\"should reduce damage by armor %\", function()\n    expect(Combat.calculateDamage(100, 50)).to.equal(50)\nend)\n\nit(\"should never go below 1\", function()\n    expect(Combat.calculateDamage(1, 99)).to.equal(1)\nend)\n\nit(\"should handle 0 armor\", function()\n    expect(Combat.calculateDamage(100, 0)).to.equal(100)\nend)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "The Golden Rule", "text": "If a function needs Roblox services to run, it's <em>hard</em> to test. If it takes plain numbers/strings/tables and returns plain values, it's <em>easy</em> to test. Separate your game into: <strong>pure logic</strong> (testable) + <strong>glue code</strong> (connects logic to Roblox)."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🔧 Mocking & Dependency Injection", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "When you <em>must</em> test code that uses Roblox services, use <strong>mocking</strong> — replace the real service with a fake one that you control."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Module that accepts dependencies (dependency injection)\nlocal LeaderboardService = {}\n\nfunction LeaderboardService.new(dataStore)\n    local self = {\n        _store = dataStore,  -- injected dependency\n    }\n    setmetatable(self, {__index = LeaderboardService})\n    return self\nend\n\nfunction LeaderboardService:getTopPlayers(count: number)\n    local ok, data = pcall(self._store.GetAsync, self._store, \"leaderboard\")\n    if not ok then return {} end\n    table.sort(data, function(a, b) return a.score > b.score end)\n    return {table.unpack(data, 1, math.min(count, #data))}\nend\n\n-- TEST with a mock DataStore:\nlocal mockStore = {\n    data = {},\n    GetAsync = function(self, key)\n        return self.data[key]\n    end,\n    SetAsync = function(self, key, value)\n        self.data[key] = value\n    end,\n}\n\nmockStore.data[\"leaderboard\"] = {\n    {name = \"Alice\", score = 500},\n    {name = \"Bob\", score = 300},\n    {name = \"Charlie\", score = 700},\n}\n\nlocal lb = LeaderboardService.new(mockStore)\nlocal top = lb:getTopPlayers(2)\nexpect(#top).to.equal(2)\nexpect(top[1].name).to.equal(\"Charlie\")  -- highest score first"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🏃 Running Tests", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Simple test runner (no framework needed!)\n-- Place in ServerScriptService as a Script\n\nlocal tests = {}\nlocal passed = 0\nlocal failed = 0\n\nlocal function test(name: string, fn: () -> ())\n    local ok, err = pcall(fn)\n    if ok then\n        passed += 1\n        print(\"  ✅ \" .. name)\n    else\n        failed += 1\n        warn(\"  ❌ \" .. name .. \" — \" .. tostring(err))\n    end\nend\n\nlocal function assertEqual(actual, expected)\n    if actual ~= expected then\n        error(`Expected {expected}, got {actual}`, 2)\n    end\nend\n\n-- Run your tests:\nprint(\"Running tests...\")\n\nlocal Combat = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.Shared.Combat)\n\ntest(\"100 damage, 0 armor = 100\", function()\n    assertEqual(Combat.calculateDamage(100, 0), 100)\nend)\n\ntest(\"100 damage, 50 armor = 50\", function()\n    assertEqual(Combat.calculateDamage(100, 50), 50)\nend)\n\ntest(\"minimum damage is 1\", function()\n    assertEqual(Combat.calculateDamage(1, 99), 1)\nend)\n\nprint(`\\nResults: {passed} passed, {failed} failed`)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "note", "title": "Test File Naming", "text": "Convention: if your module is <code>Combat.lua</code>, name the test file <code>Combat.spec.lua</code>. TestEZ automatically finds files ending in <code>.spec</code>."}]}], "quiz": {"question": "What is the main benefit of separating game logic from Roblox APIs?", "options": [{"text": "It runs faster", "correct": false}, {"text": "It makes the logic easy to unit test", "correct": true}, {"text": "It reduces memory usage", "correct": false}, {"text": "It's required by Roblox", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Pure functions (input → output, no side effects) are easy to test without needing Roblox Studio running.", "incorrect": "Separating logic from APIs makes it <strong>testable</strong> — you can test pure functions without Roblox."}}, {"id": 39, "title": "Capstone: Build a Game", "icon": "🏆", "color": "#ffd93d", "desc": "Apply everything you've learned to build a complete coin-collection game system from scratch", "sections": [{"type": "card", "title": "🏆 The Final Project", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Congratulations — you've made it to the final lesson! In this capstone, you'll build a <strong>complete game system</strong> that combines nearly every concept from the course: instances, events, client-server communication, data persistence, UI, and more."}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>What you'll build:</strong> A <strong>Coin Collection Game</strong> with:<br>• Coins that spawn, float, and spin in the world<br>• Collection with visual + sound feedback<br>• A coin counter HUD<br>• Persistent data saving (DataStores)<br>• A server-authoritative architecture (anti-exploit)<br>• A leaderboard"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "How to Follow Along", "text": "Create a new Baseplate in Roblox Studio. Add each module as we go. By the end, you'll have a working game you can publish!"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📁 Step 1: Project Architecture", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Good architecture means organizing your code so it's easy to maintain and extend. Here's our project structure:"}, {"type": "code", "lang": "text", "code": "game\n├─ ServerScriptService/\n│  ├─ GameServer.server.lua       -- Main server script\n│  └─ DataManager.lua             -- DataStore module\n├─ ReplicatedStorage/\n│  ├─ Shared/\n│  │  ├─ Config.lua               -- Game constants\n│  │  └─ CoinConfig.lua           -- Coin settings\n│  ├─ Remotes/\n│  │  ├─ CoinCollected (RemoteEvent)\n│  │  └─ GetPlayerData (RemoteFunction)\n│  └─ Assets/\n│     └─ CoinTemplate (Part)      -- Coin model template\n├─ StarterPlayerScripts/\n│  └─ GameClient.client.lua       -- Client script\n├─ StarterGui/\n│  └─ CoinHUD (ScreenGui)         -- UI\n└─ ServerStorage/\n   └─ (server-only assets)"}, {"type": "text", "value": "Remember: <strong>ReplicatedStorage</strong> = shared between client and server. <strong>ServerScriptService/ServerStorage</strong> = server only. <strong>StarterPlayerScripts</strong> = client only."}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "⚙️ Step 2: Shared Config Module", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Start with a config module that both server and client can access. This keeps all your \"magic numbers\" in one place."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- ReplicatedStorage/Shared/Config.lua (ModuleScript)\nlocal Config = {}\n\nConfig.COIN = table.freeze({\n    SPAWN_COUNT = 20,          -- coins on map at once\n    RESPAWN_TIME = 10,         -- seconds to respawn\n    VALUE_MIN = 1,             -- min coin value\n    VALUE_MAX = 5,             -- max coin value\n    COLLECT_RADIUS = 5,        -- studs to collect\n    FLOAT_HEIGHT = 3,          -- studs above ground\n    SPIN_SPEED = 2,            -- radians per second\n    BOB_AMPLITUDE = 0.5,       -- vertical bob distance\n    BOB_SPEED = 2,             -- bob cycles per second\n})\n\nConfig.MAP = table.freeze({\n    SPAWN_AREA = 100,          -- half-size of spawn region\n    GROUND_Y = 0.5,            -- ground level\n})\n\nConfig.DATA = table.freeze({\n    STORE_NAME = \"CoinGame_v1\",\n    AUTO_SAVE_INTERVAL = 120,  -- seconds\n})\n\nreturn table.freeze(Config)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "💾 Step 3: Data Manager (Server)", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "The data manager handles loading, saving, and caching player data. It uses everything from Lessons 12 and 19."}, {"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- ServerScriptService/DataManager.lua (ModuleScript)\nlocal DSS = game:GetService(\"DataStoreService\")\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\"Players\")\nlocal Config = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.Shared.Config)\n\nlocal DataManager = {}\nlocal store = DSS:GetDataStore(Config.DATA.STORE_NAME)\nlocal cache: {[number]: {}} = {}  -- userId -> data\n\nlocal DEFAULT_DATA = table.freeze({\n    coins = 0,\n    totalCollected = 0,\n    joinDate = 0,\n})\n\nlocal function deepCopy(t)\n    if type(t) ~= \"table\" then return t end\n    local c = {}\n    for k, v in t do c[k] = deepCopy(v) end\n    return c\nend\n\nfunction DataManager.load(player: Player): {}\n    local key = \"user_\" .. player.UserId\n    local ok, data = pcall(store.GetAsync, store, key)\n\n    local result = deepCopy(DEFAULT_DATA)\n    if ok and data then\n        for k, v in data do result[k] = v end\n    elseif not ok then\n        warn(`Failed to load data for {player.Name}: {data}`)\n    end\n\n    if result.joinDate == 0 then\n        result.joinDate = os.time()\n    end\n\n    cache[player.UserId] = result\n    return result\nend\n\nfunction DataManager.save(player: Player): boolean\n    local data = cache[player.UserId]\n    if not data then return false end\n\n    local key = \"user_\" .. player.UserId\n    local ok, err = pcall(store.SetAsync, store, key, data)\n    if not ok then\n        warn(`Failed to save data for {player.Name}: {err}`)\n    end\n    return ok\nend\n\nfunction DataManager.get(userId: number): {}?\n    return cache[userId]\nend\n\nfunction DataManager.addCoins(userId: number, amount: number)\n    local data = cache[userId]\n    if data then\n        data.coins += amount\n        data.totalCollected += amount\n    end\nend\n\nfunction DataManager.cleanup(userId: number)\n    cache[userId] = nil\nend\n\nreturn DataManager"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🪙 Step 4: Coin Spawner (Server)", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Inside GameServer.server.lua\nlocal RS = game:GetService(\"ReplicatedStorage\")\nlocal Config = require(RS.Shared.Config)\nlocal DataManager = require(script.Parent.DataManager)\n\nlocal coinFolder = Instance.new(\"Folder\")\ncoinFolder.Name = \"Coins\"\ncoinFolder.Parent = workspace\n\nlocal coinRemote = RS.Remotes:WaitForChild(\"CoinCollected\")\n\n-- Create a coin at a random position\nlocal function spawnCoin()\n    local cfg = Config.COIN\n    local mapCfg = Config.MAP\n\n    local coin = Instance.new(\"Part\")\n    coin.Name = \"Coin\"\n    coin.Shape = Enum.PartType.Cylinder\n    coin.Size = Vector3.new(0.4, 2, 2)\n    coin.Color = Color3.fromRGB(255, 200, 50)\n    coin.Material = Enum.Material.Neon\n    coin.Anchored = true\n    coin.CanCollide = false\n\n    -- Random position\n    local x = math.random(-mapCfg.SPAWN_AREA, mapCfg.SPAWN_AREA)\n    local z = math.random(-mapCfg.SPAWN_AREA, mapCfg.SPAWN_AREA)\n    coin.CFrame = CFrame.new(x, mapCfg.GROUND_Y + cfg.FLOAT_HEIGHT, z)\n        * CFrame.Angles(0, 0, math.rad(90))  -- rotate cylinder upright\n\n    -- Set value as attribute (server-authoritative!)\n    local value = math.random(cfg.VALUE_MIN, cfg.VALUE_MAX)\n    coin:SetAttribute(\"Value\", value)\n    coin:SetAttribute(\"Collected\", false)\n\n    coin.Parent = coinFolder\n    return coin\nend\n\n-- Spawn initial coins\nfor i = 1, Config.COIN.SPAWN_COUNT do\n    spawnCoin()\nend\n\n-- Handle collection (server-side validation!)\ncoinRemote.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, coinInstance)\n    -- VALIDATE everything\n    if typeof(coinInstance) ~= \"Instance\" then return end\n    if not coinInstance:IsDescendantOf(coinFolder) then return end\n    if coinInstance:GetAttribute(\"Collected\") then return end\n\n    -- Distance check (anti-exploit)\n    local char = player.Character\n    if not char or not char:FindFirstChild(\"HumanoidRootPart\") then return end\n    local dist = (char.HumanoidRootPart.Position - coinInstance.Position).Magnitude\n    if dist > Config.COIN.COLLECT_RADIUS * 2 then return end\n\n    -- Grant coins\n    coinInstance:SetAttribute(\"Collected\", true)\n    local value = coinInstance:GetAttribute(\"Value\") or 1\n    DataManager.addCoins(player.UserId, value)\n\n    -- Notify client\n    coinRemote:FireClient(player, value, DataManager.get(player.UserId).coins)\n\n    -- Destroy and respawn\n    coinInstance:Destroy()\n    task.delay(Config.COIN.RESPAWN_TIME, spawnCoin)\nend)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🎮 Step 5: Client Script", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- StarterPlayerScripts/GameClient.client.lua\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\"Players\")\nlocal RS = game:GetService(\"ReplicatedStorage\")\nlocal RunService = game:GetService(\"RunService\")\nlocal TweenService = game:GetService(\"TweenService\")\n\nlocal Config = require(RS.Shared.Config)\nlocal player = Players.LocalPlayer\nlocal coinRemote = RS.Remotes:WaitForChild(\"CoinCollected\")\n\n-- Animate coins (floating + spinning) on the client\nlocal coinFolder = workspace:WaitForChild(\"Coins\")\n\nRunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function()\n    local t = tick()\n    for _, coin in coinFolder:GetChildren() do\n        if coin:IsA(\"BasePart\") and not coin:GetAttribute(\"Collected\") then\n            local baseY = Config.MAP.GROUND_Y + Config.COIN.FLOAT_HEIGHT\n            local bob = math.sin(t * Config.COIN.BOB_SPEED) * Config.COIN.BOB_AMPLITUDE\n            local spin = t * Config.COIN.SPIN_SPEED\n\n            coin.CFrame = CFrame.new(coin.Position.X, baseY + bob, coin.Position.Z)\n                * CFrame.Angles(0, spin, math.rad(90))\n        end\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Proximity detection: tell server when we touch a coin\nRunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()\n    local char = player.Character\n    if not char or not char:FindFirstChild(\"HumanoidRootPart\") then return end\n    local pos = char.HumanoidRootPart.Position\n\n    for _, coin in coinFolder:GetChildren() do\n        if coin:IsA(\"BasePart\") and not coin:GetAttribute(\"Collected\") then\n            local dist = (coin.Position - pos).Magnitude\n            if dist < Config.COIN.COLLECT_RADIUS then\n                coinRemote:FireServer(coin)\n            end\n        end\n    end\nend)\n\n-- UI: update coin counter when server confirms collection\nlocal coinLabel = player.PlayerGui:WaitForChild(\"CoinHUD\"):WaitForChild(\"CoinLabel\")\n\ncoinRemote.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(collected, totalCoins)\n    coinLabel.Text = `🪙 {totalCoins}`\n\n    -- Collection feedback: flash the label\n    local original = coinLabel.TextColor3\n    coinLabel.TextColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(255, 255, 100)\n    coinLabel.Text = `🪙 {totalCoins} (+{collected})`\n    TweenService:Create(coinLabel, TweenInfo.new(0.5), {\n        TextColor3 = original\n    }):Play()\n    task.wait(1)\n    coinLabel.Text = `🪙 {totalCoins}`\nend)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🖥️ Step 6: Server Lifecycle", "content": [{"type": "code", "lang": "luau", "code": "-- Add to GameServer.server.lua:\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\"Players\")\n\n-- Player joins: load data\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\n    local data = DataManager.load(player)\n    print(`{player.Name} loaded with {data.coins} coins`)\n\n    -- Send initial coin count to client\n    coinRemote:FireClient(player, 0, data.coins)\n\n    -- Set up leaderboard stat\n    local leaderstats = Instance.new(\"Folder\")\n    leaderstats.Name = \"leaderstats\"\n    leaderstats.Parent = player\n\n    local coinsStat = Instance.new(\"IntValue\")\n    coinsStat.Name = \"Coins\"\n    coinsStat.Value = data.coins\n    coinsStat.Parent = leaderstats\n\n    -- Keep leaderboard in sync\n    task.spawn(function()\n        while player.Parent do\n            local currentData = DataManager.get(player.UserId)\n            if currentData then\n                coinsStat.Value = currentData.coins\n            end\n            task.wait(1)\n        end\n    end)\nend)\n\n-- Player leaves: save data\nPlayers.PlayerRemoving:Connect(function(player)\n    DataManager.save(player)\n    DataManager.cleanup(player.UserId)\n    print(`{player.Name} data saved`)\nend)\n\n-- Server shutdown: save everyone\ngame:BindToClose(function()\n    for _, player in Players:GetPlayers() do\n        DataManager.save(player)\n    end\nend)\n\n-- Auto-save loop\ntask.spawn(function()\n    while true do\n        task.wait(Config.DATA.AUTO_SAVE_INTERVAL)\n        for _, player in Players:GetPlayers() do\n            task.spawn(DataManager.save, player)\n        end\n        print(\"Auto-save complete\")\n    end\nend)"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "📋 Step 7: Concepts Used Checklist", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Look at everything you just used from this course! Here's a checklist of concepts applied in this capstone:"}, {"type": "text", "value": "<strong>✅ Fundamentals (Lessons 1-4):</strong> Variables, types, operators, if/else, loops, functions<br><br><strong>✅ Data Structures (Lessons 5-8):</strong> Tables, table.freeze, deepCopy, OOP with metatables<br><br><strong>✅ Advanced Luau (Lessons 9-12):</strong> Type annotations, ModuleScripts, require(), pcall error handling<br><br><strong>✅ Standard Libraries (Lessons 13-15):</strong> math.random, math.sin, os.time, string formatting<br><br><strong>✅ Roblox Core (Lessons 16-19):</strong> Instances, GetService, events (PlayerAdded, PlayerRemoving), RemoteEvents, DataStores<br><br><strong>✅ Roblox Advanced (Lessons 20-23):</strong> TweenService for UI feedback, RunService loops (RenderStepped, Heartbeat), Attributes<br><br><strong>✅ Debugging (Lesson 36):</strong> print() for logging, error handling patterns<br><br><strong>✅ Testing (Lesson 38):</strong> Config module is testable, DataManager logic separated from Roblox APIs"}]}, {"type": "card", "title": "🚀 Next Steps & Extensions", "content": [{"type": "text", "value": "Your base game works! Here are ideas to extend it and keep learning:"}, {"type": "text", "value": "• <strong>Different coin types</strong> — Silver (1 pt), Gold (5 pt), Diamond (25 pt) with different colors and sizes<br>• <strong>Power-ups</strong> — Speed boost, magnet (attract coins), 2x multiplier<br>• <strong>Sound effects</strong> — Collection sound, background music (Lesson 25)<br>• <strong>Particle effects</strong> — Sparkles when collecting coins<br>• <strong>Shop system</strong> — Spend coins on items using MarketplaceService patterns (Lesson 27)<br>• <strong>NPC enemies</strong> — Steal your coins using PathfindingService (Lesson 26)<br>• <strong>Day/night cycle</strong> — Using Lighting service (Lesson 24)<br>• <strong>Mobile support</strong> — Touch controls with ContextActionService (Lesson 31)<br>• <strong>Leaderboard GUI</strong> — OrderedDataStore top players (Lesson 28)<br>• <strong>Discord webhook</strong> — Notify when someone reaches a milestone (Lesson 34)"}, {"type": "info", "variant": "tip", "title": "🎓 You Did It!", "text": "You've completed LuaU Mastery! You now have the knowledge to build <em>anything</em> on Roblox. The best way to keep learning is to <strong>build projects</strong>. Pick an idea, start coding, get stuck, figure it out, repeat. That's how every great developer learns. Good luck, and have fun creating!"}]}], "quiz": {"question": "In the capstone game, why does the server validate the coin collection instead of trusting the client?", "options": [{"text": "It's faster on the server", "correct": false}, {"text": "The client can't access coins", "correct": false}, {"text": "To prevent exploiters from faking collections", "correct": true}, {"text": "DataStores only work on the server", "correct": false}], "correct": "Correct! Server-side validation prevents exploiters from claiming they collected coins they didn't. The server is always authoritative.", "incorrect": "The server validates to <strong>prevent exploits</strong>. Never trust the client — always verify on the server."}}]};